Commentary: India are underway! This is slightly short but there is a little shape away. Shaw goes back and looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards the leg side for a quick run.
Slightly fuller than the last ball, gets it to shape away just a little. Agarwal makes a leave.
Shorter this time and no swing on offer. It is a little too wide to make the batter play.

Angles this into the batter, he looks to swing it away from around middle and leg. It goes on with the angle though. Agarwal looks to flick but it hits the pads and goes to the keeper. He makes an appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Goes fuller this time, tempts the batter to drive who does go for it. It goes off the inner half towards mid on.
Angles the last ball into the batter, Agarwal hops and works it to mid-wicket. Just the single from the first over.
Good start for Boult! He lands it slightly fuller and outside off. Excellent seam position there. It seams in. Shaw pushes at it with hard hands but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
A couple! A full toss this time on off, it tails back in again. Shaw looks to flick, does not get it right off the middle but still hits it well enough through mid-wicket for two.
Got the first two balls to come in and this time angles it away from the off pole. Shaw pokes at it and gets beaten.
Solid! Back of a length and on off, Shaw gets right behind and keeps it out.
Nicely worked for another two! A little too straight. Shaw does not plant his front foot way too across and then works it through square leg for two.
Confusion but safe! Shorter and around off, Shaw guides it through backward point. They take one and think of a second. Agarwal is off but Shaw sends him back in time. 5 from Boult's first.
FOUR! Up and over! First boundary of the Test! It is short and a little too wide. Shaw gets on top of the bounce and cuts it over point for a boundary.
Attacks the stumps this time and lands it on middle, Shaw is solid in defense. Started off well here has the youngster.
Some outswing but the line is a little too wide outside off to make the batter play.
One more length delivery around off, Shaw pushes it to mid off.
Just a run! A little too straight this time, Shaw works it behind square on the leg side for one.
Outside off, it is not played at. Not a lot of movement for Southee so far. Both his overs have been negotiated quite easily by the Indian openers.
Lands it on a length and around off, angles it away. Shaw guides it to point.

EDGY FOUR! Through the gap between gully and third slip! Boult goes fuller this time, it is on off and angles away. Shaw looks to push at it but does so inside the line. It goes off the outside edge down to the third man fence.
Back of a length and on off, Shaw plays it late and towards point.

Close! The inswinger now, it starts around off and then comes back in. Shaw looks to play it with a straight bat but it goes off the inside edge down to fine leg. He had to hit that, had he missed, he was a goner.
That is a peach! Unplayable to be honest! It starts on off and then initially tails back in. Agarwal looks to defend but the ball pitches and then straightens. Beats Agarwal all ends up.
End of a testing over from Boult! On middle, Agarwal gets his bat down in time and keeps it out.
Back of a length and on off, Shaw keeps it out.

OUT! TIMBER! That is an absolute jaffa! Just outstanding from Southee. He has not been at his best till now but that is a gem. The length is the key here. Southee was a little too short till now. This time he goes full. It starts on middle and then tails away late. Shaw does not do a lot wrong, he plays it with a straight bat but plays the original trajectory. The ball though shapes away just enough to beat the outside edge and kiss the off pole. Shaw looked confident in the short time he stayed out there but is done in by a beauty. Early wicket for the hosts, just the start they would have wanted after electing to bowl. Replays also show that it flicked Shaw's back pad. Also, Shaw was not exactly playing with a straight bat, it was actually towards mid on. Played all around it actually. Still though, take nothing away from the delivery. Just top class.
Looks to bowl another peach! Angles this into the batter but it keeps angling away and then goes down the leg side.
Pujara is off the mark! On the pads, he works it through mid-wicket and takes two.
Goes wide of the crease and bowls it just outside off. Left alone.
On the stumps, Pujara keeps it out. End of a successful over from Southee.
Gets it to swing back in but it is on the pads, Agarwal works it through mid-wicket and takes an easy two. Gets off the mark on the 9th ball.
Probably the first short ball till now! A surprise element! Agarwal spots it early and ducks under it.
Very wide outside off, not played at.
On the fuller side and on off, Agarwal strokes it to mid off.
Length and outside off, left alone.
Squared him up there! Length and on middle, it is angled away. Agarwal is squared up as he tries to defend but plays it well towards gully.
Good swing for Southee but the line is a little too wide outside off. Pujara watches it go to the keeper.
One more length delivery outside off, left alone.
Down the leg side this time, Pujara does not play at it.
Southee goes wide of the crease but does not bowl it close enough to the stumps to make the batter play.
Attacks the stumps this time, Pujara looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards mid-wicket.
On off, Pujara keeps it out nicely.
Good running! This is on off, Agarwal drops it towards cover, takes off for one and completes it.
Very full but outside off, Pujara does not fiddle with it.
Good fielding! Full toss, wide outside off, Pujara guides it towards point. Blundell dives to his left and saves a boundary. Boult gets away with one there.
On middle, Pujara keeps it out.
On off and it comes back in. Pujara looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards fine leg for one.
Angles this one away from the off pole, Agarwal makes a leave.
Full, swinging away but wide outside off. Not played at.
On a length and around off, Pujara easily keeps it out.
Once again on the off pole and on a length. Pujara looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards mid-wicket.
Good bowling! Tim continues bowling it on a length and around off, Pujara though is playing the forward defense really nicely.
Goes wide of the crease now but bowls it wide outside off. Pujara shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! A poor ball to end a good over by Southee and it costs him a boundary! A full toss on off, Pujara hits it down to the long on fence. First for Pujara.
Good length and outside off, Agarwal points his bat skywards and lets it be.

Good shot! Just a mere push! Fuller and around off, Agarwal pushes it through mid off. Williamson at extra cover hares after it. Slides and lobs it towards Patel who runs behind him from mid on. The two can't stop the third though.
Just outside off and angles it away. Left alone.
That is a lovely nut! Changes his length, bowls it slightly short and around off. Angles away. Pujara pokes at it and gets beaten.
More runs! Fuller and on middle, Pujara pushes it past mid on and takes two.
Outside off, not played at.
Just the run! Very good fielding! On the pads, Agarwal works it through square leg and calls for two. Boult covers ground quickly to his left from fine leg and keeps the batsmen down to one.

A huge shout but not given! Just outside off and it did not come back enough. It is slightly fuller. Pujara looks to leave it but it comes in just a tad. It hits the front pad. An appeal but it is turned down. Williamson doesn't opt for the referral.
Just outside off, Pujara covers his off pole and lets it go.
Down the leg side, Pujara looks to flick but misses.
Angles this into the middle pole, Pujara works it to mid-wicket.
One more delivery on the pads, Pujara works it towards fine leg and gets to the other end.
Starts off with a length ball outside off, Pujara does not play at it.
Back of a length and on off, Pujara works it on the leg side. He thinks of one but is sent back. That hit the splice of the bat. Extra bounce for Jamieson.
Wide outside off this time and another leave by Pujara.

Wow! That is some delivery! It is angled into the off pole which means Pujara has to play at it. It then swings away late and beats the outside edge of Pujara and also the off stump by a whisker. This will give KJ a lot of confidence.
Length again but this is just outside off. Left alone.
A good over by Jamieson to begin! A maiden! Outside off, left alone.
On a length and around off, Agarwal taps it to point.
Slightly fuller and outside off, Agarwal plays it off the back foot towards point.
Huge appeal but not given. Length ball on off, it goes on with the angle and Agarwal misses his flick. He is rapped on the pads and there is some appeal from the bowler. The umpire shakes his head.
Length and on middle, tucked towards the leg side.
Good length and around middle, played towards the leg side by Agarwal.
Length and outside off, left alone.

Direct hit and that would have been very close! A shortish delivery on the body, Pujara tucks it towards square leg and takes off. Agarwal is a touch late in taking off. The fielder from mid-wicket gets to the ball quickly and underarms it towards the striker's end but misses.
Shortish and on middle, Agarwal hops and defends it onto the ground.
Another good run! On off, Agarwal pushes it towards cover for a quick run.
Outside off, not played at.
Well bowled and well played in the end! Back of a length, it is angled into the batter. It straightens a touch. Pujara does look to poke at it but in the end drops his hands.
Splice of the bat again! Shorter and on middle, Pujara looks to defend but it hits the higher part of the bat.
Agarwal takes a few steps down the track but Colin shortens his length just a little and bowls it just outside off. Left alone.
On the stumps this time, MA works it to mid-wicket.
Gets some nice shape away from the batter but the line is outside off. Not played at.
Back of a length and on middle, Agarwal keeps it out.

Ohhh! Agarwal was probably in two minds there. It is on off and then shapes away. Agarwal is not sure whether to leave it or play at it. In the end he looks to defend but gets a bottom edge which goes on the bounce to the keeper.
A dot to end a good over by Colin! On off, it is kept out.
Shortish and outside off, Pujara does not play at it.
Slips this one down the leg side. Pujara looks to flick but misses.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! An absolute gem of a delivery to get rid of Pujara. FIRST TEST WICKET FOR Jamieson and he will remember it for a long, long time. He is delighted! The tall lad has been exceptional so far and it is a well-deserved wicket. It is a length delivery. It lands on middle and then straightens. Pujara does not do a lot wrong there. He looks to play the original trajectory but the ball kisses the outside edge due to the movement and goes into the gloves of the keeper. Big wicket as CP is known to play the long innings. New Zealand are reaping the reward for bowling the right lines and lengths here. India in a spot of bother.
WIDE! Welcomes the Indian skipper with a bumper but it is way too short. Watling jumps, just gets a glove to it. Takes the pace of the delivery. The man from fine leg cuts it off and a bye is taken.
A single! Fuller and on off, Agarwal strokes it through mid off. There could have been two but Kohli slips as he took off for the first run and hence, only one.
Outside off, left alone.
One more delivery outside off, it is left alone again. End of a top over from Jamieson.
Full and angled on off, Agarwal plays it to gully.
OHH! Short of a length ball outside off, Agarwal looks to cut it but gets a bottom edge which rolls towards the keeper.
Length and around off, Agarwal comes forward and then makes a leave. A brave call though as the ball was just close to the off pole.
Length and on off, Agarwal plays it to covers off the back foot.
Length and on off, Agarwal defends it off the front foot towards the off side.
Length and around off, blocked off the back foot.
On the fuller side, Kohli shuffles across and pushes it towards covers.
A short one, Kohli spots it early and ducks under it.
Kohli is off the mark! Fuller and on middle, VK pushes it through mid on and takes two.
On the shorter side, Kohli takes one hand off the handle as he defends it.

OUT! TAKEN! Number three down and it is the biggest wicket in this Indian batting line-up. The skipper falls for a very low score. Jamieson is on fire here. Pujara first and now Kohli. The Kiwis right on top at the moment. Too early to play that shot to be honest. Especially on a wicket which is providing some assistance to the bowlers. It is slightly fuller in length, not a driving length, just behind it. Outside off and moving away. Kohli pushes at a delivery he should be leaving. It takes the outside edge and Taylor at first slip takes a simple catch in his 100th Test. The ball did not get settled into the bucket hands of Rosco but he managed somehow to hold onto it. This wicket actually reminded us of how Kohli used to get out in England in 2014. New Zealand now will be sensing an opportunity to get two more before Lunch.
Rahane is off the mark! A gift for him. A full toss on the pads, Rahane works it through mid-wicket and takes three. End of another successful over for KJ.
Rahane walks down the track and Colin lands it on middle. It is pushed back to the bowler.
Outside off, Rahane does what Kohli should have done. Left it alone.
Outside off, Rahane shoulders arms to this one.
Just outside off, Rahane walks across and lets it be.
One more delivery outside off, Rahane does not fiddle with it.
Rahane had to get bat on that! It was on middle and Rahane flicks it right off the stumps down to fine leg for one. Had he missed, he was an LBW candidate.
On the fuller side, it is pushed to mid off.
FOUR! A little too full and Rahane takes full toll of it. On middle, Rahane eases it down to the long on fence for a much-needed boundary.
Higher part of the bat! Length and on off, Rahane looks to defend but it hits the sticker and rolls towards gully.
Leading edge but a run! On the pads, Rahane is early in the flick. It goes off the leading edge towards cover for one.
Just outside off, left alone.
Goes wide of the crease and bangs it short on the body. Agarwal stays back and keeps it out.
On middle, Rahane works it to mid-wicket.
Just outside off, left alone.
On off, Rahane keeps it out nicely.
Wider outside off, Rahane watches it go to the keeper.
On the pads, Rahane works it around the corner and takes one. 50 up for India. They though have lost three wickets.
A dot to end! On off, Agarwal works it to mid on.
On the shorter side, Rahane takes one hand off the handle and keeps it out.
Slightly fuller and on off, Rahane pushes it towards cover.
On the pads, Rahane flicks it towards the square leg region for one.
On the shorter side around off, Agarwal pushes it towards cover.
Back of a length again and on middle, Agarwal stays back and keeps it out.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Just used the pace of the bowler! On the fuller side around middle, Agarwal shows the full face of the bat and creams it down to the long on fence.
On a length and around off, Rahane keeps it out.
One more length delivery around off, Rahane gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
Slips this one down the leg side, Rahane lets it be.
One more delivery on the pads, Rahane works it down to fine leg and takes one.
Another one on the pads, it is a low full toss. Mayank works it through square leg for one. Southee is looking to move the ball away from the leg pole but is not getting the movement.
On a length now and on off, Rahane gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
A bumper to begin his new spell! Agarwal ducks under it.
Nicely played! This is fuller and it is angled across the right-hander. Agarwal plants his front foot ahead and then strokes it through covers for two.
Good length and on off, Agarwal guides it towards gully.
One more length delivery around off, MA is solid in defense.
FOUR! A very confident shot! It is not a full delivery, it is a length ball. Angling away from off. Agarwal strokes it on the up through covers and it races away to the fence.
Follows the boundary with a single down to fine leg.
Outside off, not played at.
Fuller and on middle, Agarwal strokes it to mid on.

FOUR! That is a very fortunate boundary! Agarwal really played a poor shot there. It is very wide and full outside off. Agarwal reaches out for it. He plays a half-hearted stroke. The ball flies off the outside edge, between gully and third slip for a boundary.
On off, this time Agarwal is solid in defense.
Down the leg side, Agarwal looks to flick but misses.
Wide of the crease goes Southee and angles it into the off pole. Agarwal keeps it out.

FOUR! Edgy but Rahane won't mind. Length ball on off, Rahane looks to defend it but the ball goes off the outside edge and past the third slip for a boundary at third man. He controlled it well though.
Length and on off, Rahane plays it to mid off.
Full and on middle, driven to mid on.
Short of a length and on leg, Rahane takes his one hand off as he defends it to the leg side for a run.

FOUR! Another edge but once again it evades the fielder. This time it is Agarwal who gets it. Boult bowls one on the off pole and gets it to move away. Agarwal looks to defend it but the ball flies through the gap between third slip and gully off the outside edge for a boundary.
Length and on off, Agarwal plays it off the front foot towards mid on.
A short one on the body, Rahane evades it nicely.
On a length and around off, Rahane looks to defend but does so outside the line. It goes off the inner half through square leg for one.
Angled into the pads, MA works it to mid on.
On the pads, Agarwal looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. MA sets off for a run but then realizes it has only gone as far as the keeper. Gets back in.
Fuller and around off, Agarwal strokes it to covers.
A short one to end down the leg side. Left alone. Aleem Dar then looks at the square leg umpire who is walking towards the stumps at the other end and we will have another over.

BEAUTY! Boult almost has his man this time. Bowls it fuller on middle and then makes the ball to move away late. Agarwal looks to defend but gets beaten by the movement. Lucky for him that he did not edge that.
Length and on off, blocked off the front foot to the off side.
BUMPER! Rahane sees it and ducks under it.
Length ball on middle, Rahane plays it to mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Full and on off, Agarwal brings out the solid front foot defense. Last ball coming up before Lunch.
BOUNCER! Agarwal ducks under it and sees off the session. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 1!
Starts with a length ball but way outside off, Rahane makes a leave.
Full and on middle, Rahane defends it off the back foot towards the leg side.
Another one that is bowled in the channel of uncertainty. Rahane makes a leave.
Full and around off, Rahane drives it to mid on.
Good length and around off, Rahane defends it with soft hands towards covers.
Slightly back of a length ball on off, Rahane defends it off the back foot towards point. A maiden to start.
Length ball on off, played towards the leg side.
Full and on middle and leg, Agarwal plays it towards mid-wicket.
Length ball outside off, bowled from wide of the crease. Agarwal looks to defend it but the ball rears up and the keeper does well to collect it.
Length ball on off, Agarwal defends it off the back foot towards the off side.

FOUR! Jamieson strays one down the leg side and pays the price. Kyle bowls one on a length but the line is down the leg side, Mayank just helps it on its way towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Full and outside off, Agarwal lets it be.
Shorter and outside off, Rahane evades it.
Down the leg side, Rahane looks to flick but misses.
Slightly fuller around off, Rahane looks to drive but it goes off the outer half through point for two.
This is angled into the pads, Rahane stays back and keeps it out.
Bowled on the off pole, Rahane is solid in defense.
The sucker ball now! Full and wide outside off, Rahane resists the temptation and makes a leave.
Shorter and outside off, Agarwal lets it go to the keeper.
Very full and on middle, it is worked towards mid on. Boult runs to his right but fumbles and concedes a run.
Good length and outside off, Rahane covers his off pole and lets it go.
On a length and around off, Rahane prods forward and keeps it out.
A little too wide outside off, Rahane does not fiddle with it.
One more length delivery, Rahane is solid in defense.
Back of a length and on middle, Agarwal stays back and keeps it out.
One more length ball on off, MA blocks.
Good shot but for no runs! Fuller and around off, Agarwal pushes it firmly towards mid off.
A short one on the body, Agarwal ducks under it.
On the fuller side, Agarwal strokes it to mid off.

That is a beauty! Clever bowling! Goes wide of the crease and angles it into the off pole. Now, due to the angle, Agarwal is drawn into playing at it. He tries to block but the ball moves away and whizzes past the outside edge.
Outside off, not played at.
On off, Rahane strokes it to mid off.
Another delivery outside off, Rahane need not play at it.

Very well played! On the shorter side and on middle, Rahane gets on top of the bounce nicely and pulls it all along the ground through square leg. The fine leg fielder runs to his left and saves two for his side.
One more short one, this time Rahane lets it go through to the keeper.
Shorter and around off, it is guided to point.

OHH! Did that carry? Yes, it did. Boult has been brilliant with the catches in his followthrough throughout his Test career. This time also he does get the hand but fails to hold onto it. He bowls it full and on middle, Agarwal looks to flick it to the leg side but he closes the bat face early to hit it back to the bowler who gets a hand to it but fails to hold on.
Full and on off, Agarwal drives it to mid off.

OUT! CAUGHT! Boult has a big smile. He would be a relieved man. The drop did not cost him and his team much. He goes short and on middle and leg, Agarwal goes for the pull but fails to get it off the middle. Mayank plays it uppishly and the ball goes towards long leg where Kyle Jamieson runs to his left and tumbles to take the catch safely.
Length and on off, Vihari defends it off the back foot.
Length and outside off, left alone this time.
Full and outside off, Vihari pushes it through covers and gets an easy couple.
Good length and outside off, it is not played at.
Good length and around off, Rahane pushes it towards cover for a brisk single.
Yes, a short one straightaway but it is outside off. Vihari lets it go.
One more short ball but once again outside off. It is evaded again.
Almost! After two short balls, he goes full. It shapes away a touch. Vihari looks to push at it but it goes off the outer half but lands well short of gully.
Length and on middle, Vihari keeps it out.
Good length and on off, blocked.
One more length delivery around off, Rahane defends it onto the ground.
On off, AR is solid in defense.
Fullish and on off, Rahane jams it out towards cover.
Length and on off, Rahane gets right behind the line and defends.
Outside off, not played at.
BEATEN! Shorter and around off, Vihari plays inside the line and gets beaten.
FOUR! Top, top shot! Fuller and on middle, Vihari strokes it right off the middle and it races away to the long on fence. A confident stroke.
Excellent comeback! This is fuller and just behind a driving length around off. It shapes away. Vihari looks to drive again but this time gets beaten.
On off, Vihari lunges forward and keeps it out nicely.
Angles this one into the pads, Vihari looks to flick but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Outside off and it is an easy leave for Vihari.
Length and around off, Rahane defends it towards cover.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
Outside off, not played at.
On off, Rahane prods forward and keeps it out.
Shorter and on middle, Rahane ducks under it.
Fuller and on off, AR keeps it out nicely.
Back of a length and on middle, Vihari stays back and keeps it out.
On the pads, Vihari looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and rolls on the leg side for one. Leg bye signaled.
Down the leg side, left alone.

FOUR! Just over! Rahane gets away with one. He had no clue where the ball was. It is short and on the body. Rahane looks to fend at it by taking his eyes off the ball. It hits the glove and lobs over the leaping keeper and into the fine leg fence. 100 up for India.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length and on off, Rahane guides it to point.
Outside off, left alone.
On the pads, this is worked towards square leg.
Good length and on off, Vihari gets right behind the line and defends it.
Angled into the pads, HV works it down to fine leg and takes a single.
Slightly fuller and around off, Rahane looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Very full and on off, this is squeezed out towards the bowler.

OUT! Caught behind! Another one bites the dust! Jamieson bags another one. A three-fer for him. Half the side back in the hut for India and they are just over the 100-run mark. Also, a wicket immediately after Drinks, how often do we see that? It is another good delivery. On a length and around off, it holds its line. Vihari looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge. Watling dives and takes a good catch to his right.
A short one to welcome Pant. He evades it.
Good length and around off, extra bounce there. Pant does well to defend it onto the ground by taking a hand off the handle.
Well bowled! Good use of the angle there. It is on off and angles away. Pant looks to defend but is beaten.
Awkwardly played! Shorter and on the body, Pant fends at it awkwardly. It falls safe on the leg side.

Another one? No! A short one on the body, Pant looks to work it on the leg side but it hits the thigh pad and lobs towards short leg. Nicholls dives forward and takes it. A stifled appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Full and tailing away but outside off. Rahane watches it go to the keeper.
Good length and on off, Rahane keeps it out.
Gets this one to tail back in, Rahane works it with the swing to mid-wicket.
Extremely full and on middle, Rahane jams it out back to the bowler.
FOUR! Superb timing! Slightly fuller and on middle, Rahane strokes it with the full face of the bat and it races to the long on fence. Quite a few boundaries in that region today.
On the pads, it is worked through mid-wicket for one.
A short one on middle, Rahane ducks under it.
A short one on the body, Rahane mistimes his pull towards fine leg. He takes one, Boult misfields but no extra run conceded.
Back of a length and on off, Pant keeps it out.
Full and on the pads, RP looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
A short one but it is way too short. Wided.
A half-hearted appeal but turned down! A little too straight. Pant looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Seemed to be pitching outside leg.
The batsman has driven it to mid off.
Length ball angled on middle, flicked towards mid-wicket.
On a length and on middle, defended off the front foot towards the leg side.
Length ball on off, Rahane defends it off the front foot towards covers.
Length and on off, Rahane blocks it off the front foot once again.
Length and on off, Rahane keeps it out off the back foot.
Another one which is bowled on length and on middle, Rahane defends it off the back foot.
Slightly fuller and on off, Pant strokes it to mid off. He is yet to get off the mark.
Outside off, not played at.
Good length and on off, Pant keeps it out.
Pant is finally off the mark! Fuller and around off, he strokes it down the ground for a single.
Fuller and around off, Rahane eases it to covers.
Good length and on off, AR keeps it out.
Length ball and angling across the southpaw. Pant defends it off the front foot towards covers.
On a good length and on off, Pant blocks it off the back foot.
Full and angled into the pads, Pant flicks it towards mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Length ball on off, Rahane tucks it off the front foot towards square leg and calls for a single. Pant hesitates. Tom Blundell though fumbles and allows the run to be completed.
Length and around off, blocked off the front foot towards covers.
Length ball on the pads, Pant flicks it off his pads towards mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, defended.
Angled into the pads, Rahane works it towards mid on.
On the stumps again, Rahane once again works it towards mid on.
A short one and on middle, it is ducked under.
Outside off, Rahane does not fiddle with it.
Outside off, left alone.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
One more length ball outside off, not played at.
One more delivery outside off, Pant lets it go to the keeper.
Slightly fuller and on off, Pant pushes it towards cover.
Driven through mid off by the batsman.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Shorter in length and on middle, Rahane pulls it through square leg and takes one.
Outside off, Pant does not want to fiddle with it.
FOUR! Nicely played! Shorter in length and on the body, Pant swivels and pulls it down to the fine leg fence for a boundary. First for Pant.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
Around off, Pant guides it towards point.
Length ball on off and middle, defended off the back foot towards mid off.
Length and on off, AR drives it to covers.
Short and on middle and leg, pulled through mid-wicket for a single by Rahane.
Length and in that channel outside off, Pant shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length ball on off, Pant pulls it but can only get it to the man at mid on.
Length ball outside off, Pant goes chasing at it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Floats it up on middle, Rahane keeps it out.
Tosses it up on middle, Rahane is once again solid in defense.
Slower through the air and on off, AR keeps it out.
Stump-to-stump line again, it is kept out.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
On middle, Rahane prods forward and keeps it out.
On the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.
On middle, Rahane blocks it.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Fuller in length and on off, Rahane strokes one towards mid off and takes off for a run. The fielder there has a shy at the keeper's end but misses.
Full and on the pads, Pant works it towards backward square leg and gets a couple this time.
Length and on off, defended off the front foot.
Floated ball on off, defended off the front foot towards covers.
Flighted ball outside off, Rahane shoulders arms to it.
Loopy ball outside off, Rahane defends it to point off the front foot.
Turn and bounce for Patel. Floated ball outside off, Rahane lets it be as the ball spins past him after pitching.
Floated ball on off, Rahane keeps it out.
Tossed up ball on off, Rahane defends it off the front foot.
Good length and on off, it is kept out.
Excellent fielding! Shorter and around off, Pant cuts it hard. It goes towards gully where Nicholls dives to his left and saves a boundary.
Shorter and on the body, Pant is hurried on the pull. He mistimes it towards fine leg for one. Went off his gloves.
Outside off, not played at.
One more ball on a length and around off, Rahane keeps it out towards covers.
Fuller now and on off, AR strokes it to mid off. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 1!
Gets away with a loosener! Short and down the leg side. Pant looks to pull but misses.
Floats it up on middle, Pant keeps it out nicely.
Another tossed up ball on middle, Pant keeps it out nicely.

SIX! First runs of the day and it is in the form of a biggie! It is also the first maximum of the game. Pant loves playing against someone who turns the ball back into him. Uses his feet, gets to the pitch of it and tonks it well over the long on fence.
Follows the biggie with a single as this is worked through mid-wicket.
Flatter and around off, Rahane stays back and keeps it out. 7 from the first over of the day. Also, there probably will be a change from this end. Don't think Ajaz will be getting another over.
Errs in line to begin with. Slips this one down the leg side. Pant looks to flick but misses.
A little too straight, Pant works it towards square leg where the fielder dives to his left and stops it.
Shorter and outside off, Pant leaves it alone.
On the fuller side and around off, Pant plants his front foot forward and keeps it out.
Another one on a fuller length, Pant pushes it towards cover. No seam movement for Southee today till now!
Gets this one to shape back in from the middle pole. Pant though works it with the movement through mid-wicket for two. Pant has started on a positive note here.
Good running! Shorter and on off, Rahane taps it towards the off side and takes one.
That is a lovely delivery! It is a length ball, starts on off and then moves away. Pant hangs his bat out and gets beaten.
Another away-swinger but the line is outside off this time. Pant lets it be.
On the pads, Pant looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The batters think of a run but then don't go for it.
Just outside off, another leave from Pant.

Extra bounce! This lands on middle and then jags back in a little. There is also some extra bounce. Pant looks to defend but misses to get hit near the box. A good first over by Boult. He was not at his best yesterday but starts off well today.
Outside off, Rahane does not play at it.

OUT! RUN OUT! A huge, huge mix-up and Rishabh Pant has sacrificed his wicket. The last thing India wanted today. Pant was looking nice and positive today, he really gave that feeling that he is quite focused and determined to do something special but he falls in the last manner a batter would want to be dismissed. This is a back of a length delivery, Rahane guides it towards point. He takes off, he is charging towards the other end. Pant is not interested as he wants Rahane to go back although after taking a start. Till the time Rahane sees that, he is halfway down the track. He continues running and hence, Pant has to go for it. Ajaz Patel picks the ball up, he knows he has time on his hands, takes aim and hits the stumps. Pant is way short, he never had any chance of making it. Rishabh walks back disappointed and the Kiwis celebrate. Ideal start for them.

OUT! Knocks him over! One brings two and that is exactly the case for the Kiwis. A top nut to get on the first delivery! Ashwin missed that by a long, long way. He was completely bamboozled. Southee goes wide of the crease and angles it into the batter. It is on a fuller length but the ball then tails away. Ashwin plays down the wrong line and the ball clips the off pole. Two early wickets for the Kiwis and they are into the Indian tail. Can they keep India below 150?
Down the leg side, Sharma walks right across and tries to flick but misses.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Fuller and on off, Sharma strokes it to mid off. Two wickets in the over. A momentum changing one.
Good length and on off, this is guided to point.
Shorter and on the body, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
Uppish but safe and Sharma is off the mark! This is short and on the body, Sharma hops and works it uppishly but wide of short leg and through square leg for one.
Good length and on off, Rahane keeps it out.

FOUR! Up and over! A welcome boundary for India. This is full and wide outside off. Rahane goes after it. He hits it off the outer half of his bat over the point fielder and finds the fence. One would feel Rahane would take every opportunity of scoring that is offered to him.

Top edge but safe! A short one and on middle, Rahane looks to pull but fails to get on top of the bounce. It takes the top edge but falls short of fine leg. A single taken. Rahane retains strike and this ends up being a good over for India.
On a length and around off, blocked.
A sharp bumper, Rahane looks to pull but misses. Rahane has probably decided to play his shots now and rightly so.
This is angled into the pad, Rahane works it through mid-wicket for one.
OHHH! Southee goes very wide of the crease and angles it into the stumps. Ishant works it right across and flicks it towards square leg. He had to get bat to that.
Just over Blundell! A single! On the pads again, Sharma flicks it uppishly, over the outstretched hand of Tom for a run.
A short one to end! Rahane evades it. So he fails to retain strike, just what the Kiwis would have wanted.
Down the leg side, Sharma looks to flick but misses.
Nicely played! Fuller and on middle, Ishant works it through mid on for a couple.
Fuller and on the middle, Ishant stays back in his crease and gets his bat down in time.
On the shorter side this time. Ishant hops and keeps it out.
One more short ball but this is down the leg side. Ishant ducks under it.
Full again and on middle, Ishant pushes it towards extra cover.
On the fuller side and tailing away. Rahane lets it be as it is outside off.
One more bumper, Rahane ducks under it.

OUT! Rahane is out of here! The last recognized batter is gone! Southee is on fire today morning. His second wicket in this session and his third overall. India are in big, big trouble at the moment. It is a harmless delivery to be honest. It is full and wide outside off. Rahane is in two minds whether to leave it or play at it. In the end he tries to leave but it hits the inside edge and goes low towards Watling who takes a tumbling catch. A gritty knock from Rahane comes to an end but at the wrong time for India.
Shami is off the mark! On the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.

NOT OUT! Ishant survives to fight another day. Nothing on Hot Spot and nothing on Snicko. A fuller ball around off, it tails away. Ishant plays inside the line. There is a noise as the ball passes the bat. Watling takes it and then appeals. Dar thinks and then raises his finger. Ishant reviews immediately. Replays roll in and they show the noise was of the ball hitting the back pad. They then check for the LBW too but the impact is outside off. The on-field call has to be overturned. Good review by Sharma.
Fuller and on middle, this is driven down towards mid on.
Shorter and around off, Shami keeps it out.
Very full and on off, Shami strokes it nicely but to mid off.
A short one on the body, Shami decides late to pull but misses.
Slightly fuller and around off, Shami hits it nicely but finds mid off.
Handy runs! On the pads, it is a full toss. Shami flicks it through mid-wicket and takes three.
On off, Sharma gets right behind the line and defends it.
Fullish and on middle, Shami hits it to mid on.

FOUR! Streaky but India won't mind as long as they keep coming! Fuller and outside off, Shami looks to drive but it goes off the outside edge over the leaping gully fielder and down to the third man fence. 150 up for India.

DROPPED! Williamson is the culprit. How rare is that? How often do you see KW drop a catch? Don't remember the last time he did so. It is fuller and around off, Shami swings across the line. He gets a top edge which goes high in the air towards mid off. Williamson looks to take it with his fingers pointing upwards but spills it. A single taken.
On middle, this is worked towards mid on for one.
FOUR! That is right off the middle. Powerful shot. Fuller and on middle, Shami hits it hard down to the long on fence.
On off, Shami pushes it to covers. End of a very good over for India.
Length ball outside off, played to point by Ishant.
Length ball outside off, Sharma just stays on the back foot and shoulders arms to it.
On a length and outside off, defended towards point off the back foot.
Back of a length ball outside off, Sharma hops inside the crease and taps it to point.
BEATEN! Length ball outside off, Sharma goes chasing at it but misses. The ball swings away from the bat and goes past the outside edge.
Length ball outside off, Sharma is happy to let that be.
Wide outside off, left alone.
A short one now on middle, Shami is a touch early in the pull. It goes off the toe end towards the slip cordon.
Slightly fuller again around off, Shami strokes it to covers.
FOUR! Another boundary for Shami! This will be hurting Kane and really frustrating the Kiwis! A short one and on the body, Shami pulls and hits it in the gap in the square leg region.

Just safe! Shami is living dangerously here but is managing to score some handy runs! Fuller and outside off, Shami goes hard after it. He ends up slicing it just over the diving cover fielder and takes two.

In the air... safe! Shami continues to ride his luck. This is fuller and around middle, Shami swings but only manages to mistime it. It falls safe in the mid-wicket region for one. Another good over for India.
Shorter and around off, Shami guides it towards point.
Back of a length and on off, this is guided towards point for one.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Jamieson gets his fourth now! A short one just outside off, Ishant pokes at it. The ball takes the outside edge and goes into the gloves of Watling. The stand which was getting the Kiwis frustrated has been broken. Jamieson has three more balls to take a fifer on debut in this over.
Outside off, Bumrah does not play at it.
Fuller and just outside off, Bumrah does go after it but is beaten.
Misses his fifer by a whisker! Fuller again, this is angled into the off pole and then gets it to shape away. Bumrah looks to put bat on ball but the ball whizzes past the outside edge.

OUT! Shami holes out! Southee gets his man! A length ball outside off, Shami swings but only manages to hit it high up in the air towards the cover region. Blundell runs in and takes it. They go upstairs to check the back foot landing but it is fine. INDIA HAVE BEEN BOWLED OUT FOR 165!
Starts off with a length delivery around off, it angles away. Latham makes a leave.
One more delivery outside off, Latham does not play at it.
Third delivery outside off, Latham makes another leave. Bumrah is a little too short so far. He needs to get it up there if he wants to extract something from this strip.

New Zealand and Latham are underway! On the pads, Latham works it through square leg. They take two, Blundell wants the third and goes for it. Completes it with ease. Replays now show that it was uppish and was not far away from the fielder at short leg.

Nice delivery! This initially angles into the batter but then leaves Blundell. The batter thinks of playing at it but then at the very end, pulls his bat back. The length though was correct here by Bumrah. Slightly fuller.
Drags his length back a little again and it is outside off, left alone.
Starts off with a length delivery around off, gets it to shape away. Latham makes a leave.
Attacks the off pole this time. Latham defends it.
OHHH! Fuller and outside off, it shapes away. Latham is tempted to play away from his body but then at the end bails out of the shot. That is not needed, especially so early in the innings.
Bowls another one outside off, Latham this time does not go after it.
Another tempter! Full and wide outside off, Latham is not tempted and lets it go to the keeper.
That is a beauty! He angles it into the batter from around the wicket which means Latham has to play at it. Gets the ball to straighten after pitching and it beats the outside edge of the bat.
Shorter and outside off, Blundell guides it to gully. Not sure if he needed to play at that. Quite risky.
Wide outside off, Blundell this time lets it go to the keeper.
Closer to the off pole this time but not close enough to make the batter play.
This is angled into the batter, Blundell works it to short leg.
Wide outside off, another leave. Bumrah needs to attack the stumps here. At the moment, he is wasting the new ball.
Like that! Attacks the stumps, still a little too straight though. Blundell looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
On middle, Latham gets right behind the line and keeps it out.

Edged but short! Sharma lands this on off, it is on a length. It straightens a touch. Latham is half-forward as he tries to defend. He does so with soft hands and hence, the outside edge does not carry to third slip.
On the fuller side again and outside off, left alone.
This one is angled into the pads, Latham works it towards mid-wicket for one.
Just outside off, Blundell shoulders arms to this one. Ishant Sharma has really started well. He is hitting the right lines and lengths on most occasions.
Again! On the off pole and on a length. Blocked.
Now comes from around the wicket, bowls this one outside off, Latham does not play at it.
Nicely played! Does not go to the boundary but two! Full and on the pads, Latham works it through square leg.
Goes back to bowling a touch outside off, Latham once again lets it go to the keeper.
Angled into the batter, Tom nudges it on the leg side.
On the stumps, Latham keeps it out nicely.
Another couple! On the pads, Latham looks to flick but it goes off the inner half through square leg for a couple.
Good length and on off, Blundell keeps it out off the back foot.
On the pads, Blundell looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Slightly fuller and on middle, TB keeps it out nicely. Good bowling from Ishant.
In the 5th stump channel outside off. Not played at.

Gets this one to shape back in nicely but it starts from a little too close to the off pole. It ends up on the leg stump. Blundell looks to flick but misses to get hit on the thigh pad. It deflects onto the gloves and then onto his body again.
One more ball outside off, Blundell does not fiddle with it.
Length delivery and on middle, Latham defends it nicely.
Nicely timed! It still does not get to the boundary though but three taken! On the pads, Latham works it through mid-wicket and takes three.

NOT OUT! There is a huge inside edge and India lose one of their reviews. Not sure how Bumrah missed that because it was a big deflection. Can't blame Kohli here as he was behind the batter. Bumrah angles this into the batsman. It is slightly fuller. Blundell is rooted to his crease as he looks to defend but seems to have missed it. There are two noises out of which one is the ball hitting the pad. An appeal and it is turned down. Kohli, after a word with his keeper and his bowler, reviews. Replays show that the on-field call is the right one.
TB is finally off the mark and the crowd loves it. Local lad, they will probably enjoy every run he scores. On off, Blundell taps it towards the off side and takes one.
The batsman has been struck on the thigh pad.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Length ball on off, Blundell gets right behind the line of the ball and keeps it out.

EDGED AND FOUR! Blundell is lucky here. Back of a length ball around off and middle, Tom looks to flick it to the leg side but closes the bat face early to get a leading edge. It flies over the slip cordon and into the third man fence for a boundary.
Length ball around off, defended off the back foot.
Full and angling into the middle and leg stump, Blundell flicks it towards fine leg and gets to the other end.
On a good length and outside off, Latham does not fiddle with it.
Another delivery that is wide outside off, Latham lets it be to see off the session. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2!
Looks to bowl a yorker first up but ends up bowling a full toss. Blundell works it to mid-wicket.

FOUR! Off the mark in this session with a boundary! Lovely timing and placement! Yes, it is a half volley but it still has to be put away. On off, Blundell leans into it and strokes it past cover and mid off for a boundary.

Cut him into half! Excellent delivery! It is on a length and around off, it jags back in sharply. Blundell fails to negotiate the movement and it goes between the gap of bat and pad and over the middle pole.
On middle, Blundell looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards square leg for one.
From around the wicket to the left-hander, Ishant lands it on off, Latham keeps it out.
Close leave! It starts way outside off and then tails back in. Latham makes a leave. It came back in a long way and was pretty close to the off pole.
A little too straight, Blundell looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Just outside off, left alone.
Back of a length and on off, Blundell stays back and keeps it out.
On off, TB is solid in defense again.
FOUR! Crunched! Picked the length early there! It is short and on middle, Blundell rocks back and hammers the pull shot over mid-wicket for a boundary. A shot of authority. Brilliant.
After a cracking pull, offers a solid back foot defense to this delivery on off.
Slightly fuller and around off, Latham keeps it out.

OUT! Latham is strangled down the leg side! A soft dismissal but India won't care. They have got the much-needed wicket. It is down the leg side. Latham looks to flick but it goes off the inner half. Pant moves to his right and takes it. An appeal and up goes the finger. Latham walks straightaway. The front foot is then checked but that is fine. Good start after the break for the visitors. New Zealand still trail by another 139 runs.

In the air... safe! Lucky Williamson! Shorter and on the body, there is extra bounce. Williamson looks to fend but fails to get on top of the bounce. It hits the gloves and lobs on the off side. Lands safe near gully. He is in little pain at the moment.
Fuller and on middle, Williamson strokes it to mid off.
Angled into the pads, Williamson works it to square leg.
Good length and on middle, Williamson keeps it out nicely. End of a successful over by Ishant. A wicket maiden!

Safe again! Suddenly, there is something happening after the break! This is slightly short and around off, Blundell looks to work it on the leg side but closes the face of the bat a little too early. It goes off the leading edge but lands well short of mid off. New Zealand living dangerously at the moment.
On middle, this is worked towards mid on for a quick run.
Just outside off, KW covers his off pole and makes a leave.
On the shorter side and on middle, Williamson hops and works it on the leg side.
Back of a length and on off, Williamson looks to push it on the off side but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
One more length ball just outside off, Williamson lets it go through to the keeper. End of a testing over by Shami.
Outside off, Blundell lets it be.
On off this time. Blundell keeps it out.
Just outside off, Blundell prods forward and shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length and on off, Blundell goes back and keeps it out.
On middle, Blundell works it to mid-wicket.
On the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket. Maiden again by Sharma!
Short of a length ball outside off, Williamson cuts it through point and gets a couple to get off the mark.
Length and outside off, left alone by KW.
Full and angled onto the off pole, KW flicks it to mid on.
Back of a length ball on off, Kane hops inside the crease and keeps it out to the off side.
Short of a length ball on off, Williamson taps it to gully.
Full and outside off, Kane squeezes it to point.
Length delivery and outside off, Blundell lets it be.
Blundell works this with the angle towards square leg.
Back of a length and on off, Blundell stays back and keeps it out.
Good length and on middle, kept out.
Three! A little too full this time and on off, Blundell strokes it through covers and takes three. It was not hit right off the middle.
Down the leg side, Williamson looks to flick but misses.
Back of a length and on off, Blundell defends it out.
One more length ball on off, TB keeps it out nicely.
Shortish and on off, Blundell defends it onto the ground.
Outside off, not played at.
Lands it on a length again and on off, TB keeps it out.
Back of a length and on off, Tom is solid in defense.
FOUR! Nicely played! It is short and outside off, Williamson hops, gets on top of the bounce nicely and guides it past the diving point fielder for a boundary.
Good length and on off, Williamson keeps it out.
Outside off, not played at.
Back of a length and on off, KW guides it to gully.
Too wide outside off to make the batter play.
On middle, Williamson defends it nicely.
A little too straight, it is turned away nicely towards fine leg for one.
On off, Williamson plays it late and towards gully.
Well fielded! Fuller and outside off, Williamson strokes it right off the middle towards cover where the fielder dives to his left and saves a few runs for his side.
Angles this one on the off pole. Williamson keeps it out nicely.
Continues bowling it on a length and around off, Williamson looks to defend but it goes off the outer half towards gully.
Slightly fuller and outside off, Williamson shoulders arms to this one.
Lands it on a length and outside off, Blundell lets it go. It has been slow going from the Kiwis as the Indians are really bowling good lines and lengths.
Good shot! Shorter and on off, Blundell stays back and pushes it through covers for a couple.
Shorter in length and on middle, TB looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the body.

FOUR! Cracking pull shot! We have seen Blundell play a couple of excellent pull shots. He is a good back foot player and that is evident here. It is short and on middle, Blundell pulls it through mid-wicket and it races away to the fence.
Shami goes back to bowling length and outside off, it is left alone.
Shorter in length again and on the body, this is worked through square leg for a single.
On the pads, it is worked through square leg for one more run. A wild throw by Shami towards the non-striker's end. It is backed up nicely though.
Fuller and outside off, wanting Williamson to play a loose stroke. KW just lets it be.
FOUR! Another excellent shot! Shorter and around off, Williamson hops and punches it through covers. This is timed brilliantly and it races away to the fence.
Very full and on off, Williamson jams it out towards the bowler.
The batsman drives the ball straight down the ground.

FOUR! This is probably the shot of the innings so far! Exquisite! The sound of the bat meeting the ball and the balance in the shot was just brilliant. Fuller and on off, Williamson did not try to hit it too hard, he just put bat to ball, uses the pace of the bowler and strokes it through covers for another boundary. 50 up!
Play and a miss! Fuller length ball outside off, Blundell hangs his bat out to defend. The ball goes past the outside edge and into the mitts of the keeper.
Length and outside off, Blundell plays it to point.
Back of a length ball on middle, Tom flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Short of a length ball on off, KW punches it towards covers and gets to the other end.
Length and on off, Blundell defends it off the front foot.
EDGED AND SHORT! Length ball outside off, Blundell looks to defend it out but the ball goes off the outside edge towards second slip on the bounce.
Shorter and on middle, Williamson goes back and tries to flick but hits the man at short leg.
One more short ball, Williamson pushes it towards mid on for one.
Floats it up on middle, this is worked wide of mid on for another run.
Three! Slightly shorter in length and around off, Williamson makes room and pushes it through covers.
On middle, this is worked towards square leg.
A little bit of turn there! It is outside off and comes back in. Blundell plays it with the turn to square leg.
Good placement! Back of a length and on off, Williamson plays it late, he guides it through backward point and three is taken. Runs now have started to come at a quicker pace.
Back of a length and on middle, Blundell keeps it out.
Good length and on off, Blundell lunges forward and defends it.
On the shorter side again, TB is solid in defense.
On off, Blundell plays it late. It bounces behind him and goes towards the keeper.
Yes, no situation but no trouble! Shorter and on middle, it is worked towards mid-wicket. Blundell initially calls for one but then sends Williamson back in time.
Flatter on off, Williamson keeps it out.
Quicker and outside off, it turns back in. It is pushed towards cover.
On middle, it is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On middle, it is kept out.
OHHH! This is floated up on off, it turns back in. Blundell looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pads.
On the pads, it is worked through square leg for two.
FOUR! Straight down the ground! Williamson is in his elements now! On off, it is very full. Williamson strokes it down to the long off fence. The Kiwis trail by below 100 now.
Shorter and on middle, it is ducked under.
Good length and on off, KW keeps it out.
Outside off, it is left alone.
One more delivery outside off, Williamson does not play at it.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

OHHH! Close to getting a wicket. Ashwin tosses one up on off and it spins past the forward prod of Blundell. The ball goes between the bat and the body and goes over the stumps. The keeper too fails to collect it. The batsmen take a bye.
Floated ball on off, Williamson blocks it off the front foot.
Another ball that is tossed up on middle, Williamson blocks it off the front foot and into the ground.
Flighted ball on off, Kane keeps it out.
Floated on the pads, Williamson flicks it to the leg side and retains the strike.
Gets some inward movement but the line is on the pads. Williamson works it down to fine leg for one.
This tails back in again from outside off, Blundell pushes it back to the bowler.
Outside off, it is not played at.

OUT! TIMBER! Ishant Sharma gets another one! He is once again the man to provide the much-needed breakthrough. Blundell walks back after getting a start. This is a fuller delivery. It comes seaming back in from outside off. Blundell looks to defend but the ball sneaks between the gap of bat and pad and hits the stumps. Blundell was half-forward there. He needed a bigger stride to cover the movement. Replays later show that the ball clipped the back pad on its way to the stumps. India need to continue to keep chipping away at the wickets. The Kiwis trail by another 92 runs.
Length delivery and on off, it is kept out.
Taylor is off the mark! He works this one on the pads towards fine leg for one.
Very full outside off, Taylor squeezes it out towards third man for two.
Floats it up on off, Taylor is solid in defense.
Gives it air and lands it on off, RT keeps it out.
On the stumps again, Taylor blocks.
Gets off strike now as he works it through square leg.
Shorter and on middle this is pushed to long on for a single.
Length ball around off, KW defends it off the back foot towards the off side.
Full and on off and middle, Williamson taps it to the leg side off the back foot.
On a good length and outside off, Kane lifts his bat high in the air and lets the ball sail through to the keeper.
Fuller length ball around off, Kane defends it off the front foot towards point.
Length ball down the leg side, KW misses his flick and the ball goes to the keeper.
Outside off, Williamson watches the ball closely as he makes the leave.
Fuller and on off, Taylor strokes it back to the bowler.
Flatter and on off, Taylor keeps it out.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
SIX! Trademark Ross Taylor! Out comes the slog sweep. Hits it with the turn so the risk is minimum. He drags it from outside off, gets it right off the middle and clears the mid-wicket fence.
Good comeback! This is floated up outside off, it turns back in sharply. Taylor looks to defend but misses to get hit on the front pad. An appeal but it is turning down leg.
Shorter and on off, Taylor pushes it through covers for one.
This one lands around off and then jags back in. Taylor looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On middle, Taylor gets his bat down in time and keeps it out.

In the air... safe and FOUR! Taylor would have been worried for a second. It is short and outside off, Taylor looks to upper cut it but it hits the back of the bat and lobs over the keeper who runs after it. He fails to reach it and it trickles over the fine leg fence.
A single now as this is worked down to the fine leg fielder.
On the fuller side, Williamson strokes it to mid off.
This one is angled into the pads of the batter, Williamson works it through square leg and takes one.
On middle, it is worked towards mid-wicket.
Another appeal but not given! Floats it up outside off, this one also turns back in sharply. Williamson looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pads. Too high and the impact too was an issue.
Three runs! Shorter and outside off, Williamson pushes it through point and takes three.
Quicker and shorter on middle, Taylor flicks it through mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
A little too full, it is eased down to long on for one.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Shorter and outside off, Williamson lets it be.
Outside off, Williamson pushes it towards covers.
Lovely! Bumrah goes wide of the crease and then angles it into the off pole. He gets it to leave the right-hander after pitching. Williamson looks to defend but is beaten.
Outside off, not played at.
Outside off again, Williamson makes another leave.
On off this time. KW keeps it out.
On middle, this is hit down to long on for one.
On the shorter side, Williamson pushes it to the fielder at cover.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads but not in the gap.
On middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket.
On off, Taylor defends.
On off, defended again.
Slightly fuller and on off, it is stroked towards covers.
FOUR! 100 up for New Zealand! Shortish and outside off, a little bit of width on offer and Williamson pounces onto it. He plays it nice and late through backward point for a boundary.
On off, defended.
Full again and on middle, this is hit back to the bowler.
On the middle stump, Williamson keeps it out easily.
Another two! Shorter and around off, Williamson pushes it through covers and takes a brace.
Flatter and on middle, defended.
Floats it up on middle, Taylor keeps it out.
Loopy ball on off, Taylor defends it off the front foot.
Another tossed up ball on middle, Ross blocks it off the front foot.
Floated ball on off, Taylor keeps it out.
Floated ball on off, driven to mid on.
On the pads, Williamson works it to square leg.
On a length and around middle, Williamson plays it nice and late under his eyes. The ball hits the bat, hits the ground and then his pad.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Fuller and on off, Williamson strokes it wide of mid off and gets to the other end.
On the stumps again, Taylor defends it towards mid on.
A good bumper to end the over but Taylor ducks under it.
Floats it up on off, Williamson works it with the turn towards short leg.
Shorter and around middle, Williamson works it around the corner and gets off strike.
On the pads, Taylor works it to leg slip.
Misread the length there! It is floated up on off, Taylor goes back to play it. He does well to get his bat down and keep it out.
On middle, RT keeps it out.
In the air... wide! It was off the pad though. On middle, it turns into the batter. Taylor looks to flick but it hits the pad and goes on the leg side for one. Leg bye signaled.
On the off pole, Taylor keeps it out.
Once again attacks the stumps, Taylor though gets his bat down in time and keeps it out.
On off, Taylor prods forward and keeps it out.
A length ball on off, Taylor stays and defends it to cover-point.
Bouncer around middle and leg, Rosco ducks at the last second.
FIVE WIDES! Bumrah digs in a short ball around off, Taylor ducks and it shoots over to beat the jump of Pant. Bonus runs for New Zealand!
FOUR! Wow, what a way to close the session! Fuller in length and outside off, Taylor unfurls a beautiful cover drive to find the fence. TEA ON DAY 2!
Floats it up on off, Williamson keeps it out.
Gives it a lot of air and lands it around off, KW strokes it wide of the fielder at mid off and gets to the other end. First run of the session.
On off, Taylor plays it with the turn on the leg side.
Flatter and on middle, RT works it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Clever! The leg slip is now not in place so out comes the paddle sweep. Taylor plays it nice and fine on the leg side and bags a boundary.
On off, Taylor keeps it out.
Starts off with a delivery wide outside off, Williamson guides it towards gully.
Length and outside off again. It is left alone.
On off, Williamson plays it late and towards gully.
Short and on off, Williamson pushes it towards the man at covers.
On middle, KW gets right behind the line and defends it.
Another defensive stroke to this ball on off. Maiden from Shami.
Loopy ball on off, it turns back in. Taylor looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards short leg.
On middle, it is eased down to long on for one.

FOUR! Fifty for Williamson! A very solid knock from him so far. He has looked really assured and now would be eyeing a big one. Gets there in style. He steps out and gets to the pitch of it. Whips it with the turn over mid-wicket and bags a boundary. His 32nd in the format.
On middle, kept out.
Outside off, Williamson pushes it through covers for one.
The last ball is worked towards square leg.

FOUR! You need not run for that. Not a soul moved to chase that down. Right from the moment it left the bat, it was certain it is a boundary. Full and wide outside off, Williamson creams it through covers and the ball races away to the fence.
Fuller and on off, it is hit towards mid off.
On middle, it is defended onto the ground.
Back of a length and on off, Williamson guides it to point.
On off, Williamson stays back and blocks.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
On the pads, Taylor works it through square leg for one.
On middle, Williamson works it with the turn towards short leg.
Big turn! Shorter and outside off, it turns back in. Williamson initially wanted to cut but then adjusts and pushes it to the man at covers.
FOUR! Slaps this one hard for a boundary! This is a nothing delivery. Short and outside off, no turn here and it sits up to be hit. Williamson smashes it through covers for a boundary.
Now a run! Ashwin bowls another short one  outside off, it is cut behind point for a single.
On off, blocked.
Fuller and on middle, this is driven to mid on.
On the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
FOUR! Poor from Shami! He has a off side heavy field but sprays this on the pads. Taylor works it fine on the leg side and it races away to the fence.
Goes back to bowling length and on off, it is kept out.
BEATEN! Slightly short and outside off, Taylor goes after it but does not connect. That was a little too close to play that shot.
On a length and around off, Taylor drives it on the up and hits it to covers.
Good length delivery on off, Williamson punches it to the off side.
Length delivery on middle, Kane turns it towards square leg and gets a single.
Good length ball coming in with the angle. Taylor defends it towards mid on.
On the pads, Taylor flicks it towards backward square leg for a single.
Length ball outside off, Taylor defends it with straight bat.
Good length delivery on off, Williamson blocks it to get through the over.
FOUR! Creamed! Williamson played one through that region earlier but this is better. Slightly fuller and around off, Taylor strokes it through covers and it races away to the fence.
Well bowled! Bowls the yorker, Taylor jams it out.
On a good length around off, it is kept out.
Short and on middle, Taylor ducks under it.
Loose stroke! This is fuller and shaping away from outside off. Taylor's feet move nowhere and he goes for the drive but gets beaten.
Fuller and on middle, Taylor works it to mid on.
Outside off, not played at.
Good stop! Fuller and around off, Williamson strokes it nicely towards cover where the fielder dives to his left and stops it.
Good length and on off, Williamson stays back and keeps it out.

FOUR! 150 up with a delightful stroke! There are three fielders in the cover region. One at short covers, one at normal covers and the other at extra cover. Williamson still manages to find the gap as he strokes this full ball through that region and it races away.
Almost does it again! Fuller and around off, Williamson strokes it towards cover where the fielder again dives to his left and stops it.
Short ball and on middle, it is ducked under.
The batsman gets a leading edge on that one.
On the pads, this is clipped around the corner for one.
Outside off, not played at.
On the pads, this is clipped around the corner for one.
On middle, KW pushes it to mid off.
Outside off, Williamson does not fiddle with it.
A huge shout but too high! On a length and around off, it jags back in after pitching. Taylor looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Length again, this pitches and then straightens. Taylor looks to block but it goes off the outer half towards point.

EDGY FOUR! The trail now below 10. Shorter and outside off, Taylor looks to cut but there is not enough room to play that shot. He gets an inside edge which just goes past the off pole and down to the fine leg fence.
A couple now! Very full and outside off, Taylor squeezes it out nicely through backward point for two.
Well bowled again! This is on a length and around off, straightens after pitching. Taylor plays inside the line and gets beaten.
On off, defended.
On the pads, this is worked towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Up and over! Width on offer and Williamson makes Ishant pay. He cuts it over the fielder at point and it races away to the fence.
Shorter and on middle, it is kept out.
Outside off, left alone.
A single now as this is worked towards wide mid on.
Full and on middle, it is stroked to mid on.
On middle, Williamson gets right behind the line and defends it onto the ground.
Crisp! On a length and around off, Williamson strokes it nicely but straight to covers.
Angled into the middle pole, Williamson keeps it out again. There is absolutely nothing happening off the wicket here. Very tough for the bowlers at the moment.
On middle, Taylor works it through square leg for two. NEW ZEALAND ARE NOW INTO THE LEAD!
Just short! Just behind a driving length and on off, Williamson strokes it back uppishly but well short of the bowler.
Good length and on off, Williamson keeps it out.

OUT! TAKEN! A wicket completely against the run of play! Once again it is Ishant Sharma who strikes with his big booming inswinger. It is on a length and it comes back in. There is extra bounce. Taylor looks to keep it out but the ball hits the glove and lobs towards Pujara at backward square leg. He was actually taken by surprise by the extra bounce and then could not deal with it. End of the 93-run stand. Taylor departs 6 short of a half ton. A good innings by him though.
BEATEN! This is on a length and around off, it shapes away. Nicholls looks to defend but is beaten.
Good length and on off, Nicholls is solid in defense.
On middle, Nicholls works it towards mid on.
Fuller and outside off, HN leaves it alone.
Just outside off, left alone.
Flatter and on off, it is worked to mid-wicket.
On off, Williamson pushes it towards covers.
On middle, Williamson goes back and works it to mid-wicket.
A little too short this time, Williamson works it through square leg for one.
Quicker and on off, Henry goes back and pushes it back to the bowler.
The slider on off, HN stays back and keeps it out again.
Shortish and outside off, this is guided down to deep point for one.
Outside off, left alone.
Uppish but safe! Fuller and on middle, Henry Nicholls chips it over the bowler's head. He did not chip it, he was a touch early in the shot and hence, it went uppishly over mid on for two.
Good length and around off, Nicholls lunges forward and keeps it out nicely.
Outside off and on the shorter side. HN plays it with soft hands towards point.
The last ball is a harmless one, outside off and it is left alone.
On the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Well bowled! Slower through the air, it lands on off and then turns away. Nicholls goes back and tries to defend but is beaten by the turn.
Loopy ball on off, HN keeps it out.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On the stumps, defended.
Outside off, this is left alone.
On the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.
A length ball around off, Nicholls pushes it with an angled bat to point.
Chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.

Fuller length ball on off, Henry is on the front foot as he drives it back to the bowler. Bumrah collects the ball and mimes a throw at the striker's end. Signs of frustration? You usually don't see Jasprit do that!
Angling into the batsman from around off, Nicholls is behind the line in defense.
Nicholls has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Outside off, a little too wide to make Williamson play.
Loopy ball on off, this is hit through covers for one.
Quicker and on middle, the batter goes back and keeps it out nicely.
Loopy ball on middle, Nicholls prods forward and defends.
Another tossed up delivery on middle, it is kept out.
The last ball is worked towards mid-wicket.

Direct hit and it would have been close. Full on off, Williamson flicks it towards mid-wicket and calls for a quick run. Substitute Jadeja gets to the ball quickly and has a shy at the keeper's end but misses.
Good length ball outside off, Nicholls leaves it alone.
Fuller on off, Nicholls defends it with a dead bat.
Length ball on middle, Nicholls punches it towards mid on for a single.
FOUR! Bad ball and Williamson gets a boundary. Down the leg side, Williamson flicks it fine down the leg side and fetches himself a boundary.
On off, Kane blocks it.
Floats it up on middle, defended.
On middle, kept out.
Flighted ball and on off, Nicholls is solid in defense.
The batsman works it down the leg side.
Flatter and outside off, it is pushed through covers for one.
No run.
Good length ball on off, Nicholls defends it.
Outside off, Nicholls leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Henry Nicholls shoulders arms to it.
Length ball outside off, this one swings away late on, Nicholls has no business with it.
Another one outside off, Nicholls shoulders arms to it.
Fuller on off, Nicholls pushes it to mid off.
Floated off spinner on off, Williamson tucks it to the leg side.
Flighted on off, Kane looks to defend it with soft hands but it goes towards cover off the leading edge.
Flighted on off, Kane looks to defend it with soft hands but it goes towards cover off the leading edge.
Flatter on off, Williamson strokes it towards cover for a single.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball.
Shorter on off, Nicholls punches it to the off side.
On the pads, Williamson flicks it to the leg side.
Length ball on off, Williamson dabs it through backward point and gets a couple.
A short ball, outside off, Williamson rocks back and pulls it over square leg for a couple.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ravindra Jadeja, the substitute, gets into action. One of the rare errors from the New Zealand skipper. The ball is a full one, outside off, Williamson leans and drives. The shot is uppish though, as the bat turns in his hand. The ball goes towards short extra cover where substitute Ravindra Jadeja takes it sharply. Big, big wicket. A century was there for the taking.
A bouncer to the new batsman, ducked under.
A short ball, outside off, Watling ducks again.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Down the leg side, flicked to the leg side but off the pads.
Full and down the leg side, for a single.
Around off, defended watchfully.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Outside off, tapped through point for a single.
A length ball, outside off, defended watchfully.
On a good length outside off, watchfully defended.
Outside off, blocked solidly.
A bouncer on middle, ducked under.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Landed outside off, left alone.
Full and around leg stump, swept through square leg for a single.
Full and outside off, this is pushed through the covers for a run.
Landed outside off, watchfully defended.
Full and down the leg side, another sweep comes out, this time for one.
Around off, well blocked out.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
On a length, around off, solidly defended.
FOUR! A freebie. A genuine half volley, around middle, Nicholls flicks it wide of mid on. Shami does not even bother to chase.
Full and outside off, pushed straight to cover.
Landed outside off, left alone.
On a good length around off, let through to the keeper.
Around off, well blocked out.
Full and outside off, watchfully defended.
Full and straight, flicked towards short leg.
Fired in outside off, watchfully defended.
Excellent shot. Full and outside off, Watling leans and flicks it through mid-wicket. Jasprit Bumrah runs to his right from mid on and keeps the batsmen to a couple.
Around off, blocked in front of short leg.
Full and outside off, pushed to the off side.

FOUR! Great shot. But what kind of fielding was that? Tired bodies. Full and around middle, Nicholls drives it straight down the ground. Shami leaps but the ball goes over his jump. Ishant Sharma gets across from mid on but does not even bother to dive or even slide. Ashwin from mid off stops, assuming that the ball will be stopped. But now, has to run to stop the ball. In vain.
On middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
Another flick, another single.
Landed outside off, left alone.
Full and straight, watchfully defended.
Outside off, left alone.

Short and outside off, Watling rocks back and cuts it through point. A tired fielder dives to his right but misses. Cheteshwar Pujara hobbles after it from cover-point and gets to it as the ball stops. Three runs taken.
On middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
Around off, whipped through mid-wicket for a run.
Full and around middle, watchfully defended.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! India getting some wickets before the close. Plenty of turn already on this surface. Landed around middle, Nicholls looks to defend but the ball spins away and that beats him. The outside edge is taken and the ball flies straight to second slip. Good sharp catch by Virat Kohli. Ashwin has his first.
Full and outside off, watchfully defended.
Around off, defended watchfully.
On middle and leg, flicked towards square leg.
Full and around middle, flicked towards short leg this time.
Way down the leg side, left alone.
On middle, worked through mid-wicket for a run.
FOUR! In the gap. A short ball, outside off, de Grandhomme punches it through the covers. Two fielders run after it but in vain.
EDGED, FOUR! How has that gone through? Full and outside off, Watling looks to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge, along the ground and between second slip and gully to third man!

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! India could not have asked for a better start to the day's play. Wow! Bumrah has finally, finally taken a wicket, he had to wait for 48.1 international overs to get it. It is a short ball outside off, a harmless delivery to be honest. Watling could have easily left it but instead he pokes at it. The ball goes off the outside edge and Pant takes a decent catch to his right. There was some extra bounce too. Big blow to the Kiwis. Can India now keep the lead under 75?
Fuller and around off, Southee strokes it towards covers.
Good length and outside off, Southee looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards the leg side.
One more length delivery around off, Southee keeps it out.
BEATEN! On a length and outside off, Southee looks to push at it but gets beaten.
