First run today! Good fielding! Full and on the pads, Colin works it towards mid-wicket where the fielder dives to his left. He gets a hand to it. Saves a run at least.
Length and it comes back in from outside off. Southee looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On off, Southee pushes it to mid on.
A little too straight this time, Southee works it around the corner and takes one. He is off the mark.
On the fuller side, Colin de Grandhomme pushes at it but it goes off the outer half towards cover.
On the pads, Colin works it straight to the fielder at short mid-wicket.
FOUR! Lovely shot to score the first boundary of the day! Shorter and around off, Southee stands tall and pushes it through covers. It is right off the middle and it races away to the boundary.
Looks to repeat what he did on the last ball but this time he pushes it towards the man at covers.
One more length delivery around off, Southee plays yet another good looking stroke but this time only for a single towards mid off.

One more length ball outside off, Colin guides it through point and gets to the other end. This is the thing about the two, they will look to score. So, runs will come thick and fast while the two are out.
OHHH! Length delivery, a little too wide outside off, it pitches and jags back in. Southee pushes outside the line and gets beaten.
Back of a length and on off, Southee keeps it out. A good over for the Kiwis.
Outside off, left alone.
Slightly shorter in length and outside off, Colin cuts it through point. There is a fielder in the deep so just one.

OUT! TAKEN! That is a soft, soft dismissal. Southee will be gutted with himself at the moment. India are right back in this with two early wickets today morning. That is way down the leg side. Southee flicks it uppishly but towards fine leg. Shami runs in and takes the catch easily. The lead is only 60. Three wickets more for India to take. One more wicket needed for Ishant to complete his fifer.
A shortish delivery to the new batter. He sways out of the way.
Jamieson is off the mark! First run in Tests for him. On off, Jamieson pushes it towards cover for one.
Full and wide outside off, Colin watches it go through to the keeper.
On middle, Jamieson pushes it past the bowler and towards mid on and takes one.
Goes wide of the crease and angles it into the off pole. Colin defends it out.
One more delivery angling into the batter, Colin tries to keep it out but it goes off the inner half towards mid-wicket.

NOT OUT! Missing the leg pole! The Kiwi dressing room will breathe a huge sigh of relief. It did seem a marginal call, at the most it would have been clipping the leg pole. It though is missing it by some distance. A good review by Colin. Bumrah angles it into the batter, de Grandhomme looks to play it with a straight bat but misses to get hit on the pad. An appeal and up goes the finger. Colin de Grandhomme reviews. Replays roll in and they show that the on-field call has to be overturned.
Length and on off, it is pushed towards mid off.
On a length again, Colin keeps it out.
On a length and around off, Jamieson keeps it out.
Fuller and around off, it tails back in late. Jamieson looks to flick but it goes off the inner half through mid-wicket for one.

NOT OUT! It is off the pad! Never seemed out to be honest and even the sound was not woody! It is down the leg side. Colin de Grandhomme looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Pant takes it and appeals. The umpire shakes his head. Kohli and Ishant are heard saying they heard two noises and they challenge the decision. Replays roll in and they show there is no bat at all. India lose both their reviews.
BEAUTY! This is angled into the off pole and the bowler gets it to straighten after pitching. Colin's outside edge is beaten as he tries to defend.

FOUR! Powered! Stand and deliver stuff! A little too full, right in de Grandhomme's arc. He smashes it through mid off and bags a boundary. Probably that is the way Colin should play and that is what his actual game is.
Two taken! Full and on the pads, Colin works it wide of the fielder at deep mid-wicket and comes back for two.
Good length and on off, KJ guides it to point.
Good length and around off, it is defended nicely.

SIX! Goes all the way! This guy can bat and hit it big, we saw that in one of the ODIs too. A short one, Jamieson picks the length early and pulls it high and over the mid-wicket stand. Absolutely dispatched!
Goes back to bowling a fuller length. Jamieson keeps it out.
Well bowled and well played! A yorker now by Shami on middle, it is jammed out nicely. The big man gets his bat down in time quickly.
On a length now and on middle, KJ blocks it quite comfortably.
Outside off, it is not played at.
A bumper now on middle, it is ducked under.
In the air... short! On the body and it is short. Colin de Grandhomme looks to pull but does so awkwardly. It hits the splice and lands well short of fine leg. A run taken.
Angled into the batter, KJ works it to mid-wicket.
Very full and on middle, it is hit down to mid on.

FOUR! Do not bowl short to Jamieson, he will pull you to the boundary every single time. Short and on the body again. KJ swivels and pulls it behind square on the leg for another boundary. Runs flowing at the moment. Lead now 20 short of 100.
Shortish in length and on off, it is pushed through covers for one.
Well fielded! Length ball and around off, KJ strokes it on the up towards covers. The fielder dives to his left and gets a hand to it. Can't stop the single though.
One more easy single! Outside off, Colin plays it late through backward point for one.
On the pads, Jamieson looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads. It rolls on the leg side for one.
Good length and on off, it is kept out.

Back of a length delivery and on off, it is guided through point for one. 250 up for the Kiwis. Good recovery by them after losing two wickets in no time today morning. They need to keep going though.

FOUR! Poor ball to begin with the second new ball! Full and on the pads, Colin just puts bat to ball and works it through mid-wicket. It is the new ball so it races off the bat and through the field for a boundary.
Good length and on off, Colin de Grandhomme keeps it out.

FOUR! Second boundary in the over and this is even better than the last one. The lead is now into the 90s. Full and on middle, Colin de Grandhomme shows the full face of the bat and strokes it past the diving mid on fielder.
A short one now, CdG ducks under it.
Length delivery outside off, it is left alone.
One more ball on a length. It is kept out nicely.

DROPPED! A lazy effort to be honest by Shami. He could have put in a dive there. It is short and around off, Jamieson looks to defend but it hits the splice of the bat and lobs to the right of Shami. He stretches his right hand out but the ball brushes the fingertips. The dive was needed there.
Length and around off, Jamieson looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge and down to the fine leg fielder for one.
One more length ball around off, Colin de Grandhomme looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Another length ball around off, Colin de Grandhomme keeps it out.
Fuller in length and on middle, this is worked towards the man at mid on.
On the pads, it is worked through mid-wicket for one.
One more delivery on a good length. Blocked.
Slightly fuller this time, Colin strokes it square on the off side for one.
Thick outside edge for one! On the fuller side again, KJ looks to drive but it goes off the outer half towards deep point for one.
A short one and on the body, CdG ducks under it.
One more bumper on middle, it is ducked under again. It has been wided.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Length again, it is kept out nicely.
Good running! On the fuller side and on off, it is jammed to the right of mid off for an easy run.
Length delivery and on off, Colin de Grandhomme keeps it out.

This one is angled into the batter, Colin de Grandhomme looks to defend but it goes off the inner half through square leg for one. The lead is now 100. That did not look possible at the start of the day. They still have three wickets in hand.
TOP EDGE AND SIX! Jamieson continues to play freely! One more short ball and on middle, he takes on the challenge of pulling it. It goes off the top edge, over the keeper and over the fine leg fence.
He was in two minds there! It is slightly shorter and outside off, KJ is initially tempted to pull but then bails out and defends it.
Good length and around off, Jamieson pushes it towards covers.
Shorter and on middle, Colin de Grandhomme works it through mid-wicket for one.
Tosses it up around off, blocked.
Flatter and around off, kept out.
On the pads, Jamieson looks to go big but it goes off the inner half towards square leg.
Quicker and on off, it is pushed back to the bowler.
Slower through the air and on the pads, Jamieson looks to go big once again but misses to get hit on the pads.
Back of a length around off, Colin de Grandhomme looks to defend but it goes off the outer half through point for one.
One more length ball around off, KJ pushes it towards covers.
Length and on off, it is kept out.

That shot deserved a boundary! Nevertheless, three handy runs. It also brings up the 50-run stand. Vital one for the Kiwis and a frustrating one for the visitors. Because of this stand, the hosts have taken their lead above the 100-run mark. It is full and around off, Jamieson creams it through mid off and takes three.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
One more length delivery around off, blocked.
Down the leg side, KJ goes after it but misses.
SIX! This has been nailed! He has picked the bones out of this one. Ashwin tempts Jamieson by tossing it up outside off. Jamieson goes with the turn and slogs it well over the mid-wicket stand.
Flatter and on middle, it is kept out.
SIX! Another huge one! KJ is dealing in biggies. Ashwin once again tempts him by giving it a lot of loop. Jamieson swings, connects well again and it goes well over the mid-wicket stand again.
Goes around the wicket does Ashwin. He gets it to drift away from the batter. It lands on off and then goes away with the angle. KJ tries to put bat on ball but misses.
On off, kept out safely.
Length ball nipping back in, Colin blocks it off the front foot towards covers.
Length ball on off, de Grandhomme blocks it off the back foot.

Edged but just short! Brilliant bowling this from Bumrah. He bowls one on a fuller length and outside off, inviting the drive from de Grandhomme. Colin obliges and plays the drive without any footwork. The ball takes the outside edge and flies towards first slip. Virat Kohli goes for the catch by going to his left but the ball drops just short of him.
Length ball and outside off, de Grandhomme lets it be.
Short of a length ball on off, Grandhomme defends it right off the middle of the bat.
Length ball around off, Colin keeps it out off the front foot.
On the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.
Floats it up on off, Colin pushes it back to the bowler.
Shorter and on middle, it is once again pushed back to the bowler.
A single now as this is worked through mid-wicket.

Just over! This is on middle, Jamieson flicks. He seems to be a touch early in the shot and hence gets it a lot straighter than he would have wanted to. Luckily for him, it goes over the mid-wicket fielder for one.
The batsman has played it towards mid-wicket.
Length and on off, driven straight to mid off.
Full and angled into the pads, Jamieson flicks it through wide mid on and gets three.
Short of a length ball outside off, CdG cuts it through point for a single.
Brilliant yorker and brilliantly played too. De Grandhomme digs it out.
Length ball on off, Jamieson blocks it to the leg side.
Slower length ball on off, Kyle plays it out off the front foot towards point.
On middle, this is eased down to long on for one.

OUT! Jamieson holes out! End of a brilliant partnership and an entertaining innings from KJ. He goes back 6 short of a half ton. Nevertheless, this innings will surely be remembered. Ashwin tosses it up and lands it on middle. He wants KJ to go big. Jamieson obliges and looks to slog it over the mid-wicket fence but does not time it well. Vihari at long on runs to his right and takes a good catch. Can India now take the remaining two wickets quickly? Will we see Colin de Grandhomme throw caution to the wind now?
On middle, it is kept out.
On middle, defended again.
Shorter and around off, CdG stays back and defends it.
On middle, defended.

FOUR! Streaky! New Zealand won't mind though. 300 comes up. On a length and around off, it skids through. Ajaz is a little late in bringing his bat down. It goes off the inside edge, past the leg pole and down to the fine leg fence.
Length ball around off, Patel looks to defend it but gets an inside edge on it onto the pads.
Full and outside off, Patel digs it out.
BUMPER! Patel does well to sway away from the line.
Short ball on middle, Patel does well to sit under it.
Short of a length ball outside off, Patel looks to cut it but there is no room to play that shot. He still goes through with it and gets a bottom edge past the stumps towards the right of the keeper.
On middle, it is worked through square leg. It is in the gap and two taken.
FOUR! Over the head of the fine leg fielder who is quite ahead of the ropes! On the pads, Colin plays the slog sweep. It goes over that fielder's head and into the fence.
Another couple now! So de Grandhomme's intentions are clear. He is going for it. Comes down the track and swings but it goes off the inner half down towards fine leg for two.
Takes a single now as he pushes it down to long on. Good batting, already nine from the over so he need not take another risk.
Outside off, left alone.
Floats it up on middle, blocked.
Down the leg side, Colin looks to flick but misses.
Length ball around off, Colin blocks it solidly off the front foot.
On a good length and outside off, CdG lets it go through to the keeper.
Fuller length ball around off, de Grandhomme keeps it out off the back foot.
Full ball on middle and leg, Colin flicks it to mid-wicket.
Full and on off, it's driven straight through mid off and Colin keeps the strike.
Quicker and flatter on off, Colin pushes it to the left of the bowler who fields it.

OUT! Wow, just wow! Take a bow Colin de Grandhomme. You might be wondering why I'm praising Colin de Grandhomme when he has got out... Reason - He has walked. The umpire wasn't going to give him out there, India had no reviews left but Colin de Grandhomme straightaway starts walking. Ashwin tosses it up and bowls it down the leg side. Colin looks to flick but it jumps and kisses the gloves. Pant takes a fine reflex catch to his left and is appealing. The umpire initially is unmoved but de Grandhomme walks. After that the official raises his finger. A very handy innings from him comes to an end. Can India now bowl out New Zealand before Lunch?
Boult is off the mark! He comes down the track and pushes it towards cover for one.
Outside off, it is left alone.
On middle, Patel is solid in defense.
On middle, Patel keeps it out nicely.

FOUR! Flat-batted! Boult is probably going to enjoy himself out there. He clears his front leg and Ishant bangs it short. Boult smashes it past mid off and then also holds the pose for the cameras. Excellent stuff. 150 is the lead now.
Clears his front leg again and swings but misses this short ball outside off.
Another swing and a miss! Full and wide outside off, Boult swings again but misses again.
This is angled into the batter, Boult pushes it back to the bowler. Sharma followed him there.
More runs! Frustrating runs for India! A slower one on middle, Boult waits for it this time and lofts it over mid off. Not right off the middle but hit well enough for two runs.
On the pads, this is worked towards fine leg for one. He retains strike.
FOUR! Swatted! Boult comes down the track and Ashwin floats it outside off. Boult drags it through mid-wicket and bags a boundary.
Follows the boundary with a single as this is eased through covers for one.
Flatter and on middle, defended.
Slower through the air and on off, Patel keeps it out.
Another tossed up ball on off, blocked.
Slower through the air again and on middle, defended.
Boult makes room again and Sharma follows him with a short one. TB swings but misses.
Nicely played! He shuffles across this time and Ishant bowls it on off, Boult guides it through point and takes two.

DROPPED AND FOUR! That though was smashed back towards Sharma but it had to stick. It is on a length and around off, Boult thwacks it off the middle towards Sharma. It is to his left. He gets two hands to it but spills it and it races to the long off fence.
FOUR! Top edge this time! Boult is dealing in boundaries! He clears his front leg again. Sharma bowls it short. TB looks to pull but it goes off the top edge and to the fine leg fence.
Now works it through square leg and takes one. This will really be frustrating India at the moment.
Ajaz keeps out the one ball he had to face! On a length and around middle, defended.
Comes down the track but does not get to the pitch of the ball entirely. It is kept out.
Bowls the one that goes away from the batter. It lands on off. Boult looks to drive but is beaten.
Once again Boult skips down the track but does not get to the pitch of it. Defended.
SIX! This time he smokes it! Gets to the pitch of it and smashes it well over the long on fence. The way Boult is batting, he might take the Kiwi lead above 200.
On middle, defended.
A single now as this is pushed towards cover. Boult keeps strike again.
FOUR! Low full toss on middle and leg, Boult makes room and swats it through cover-point for a boundary. Brilliant batting from the Kiwi.
Short ball on off, Boult pulls it but cannot get it off the middle. It goes to mid on and the batsmen cross ends.
Length and around off, Patel defends it towards covers.
Full and outside off, Patel drives it with power but only to find mid off to perfection.
Short ball on off and middle, Patel swings wildly but fails to get anything behind that shot as the keeper collects it.
Short ball once again, Patel does well to evade it.
Short ball on middle, Boult hooks it towards deep square leg and gets a couple.

OUT! CAUGHT! The change of end works in favour of Ishant Sharma and India. He also gets a 5-fer, his 11th in this format. Brilliant bowling from him. Sharma bowls short and on middle, Boult looks to fend it away this time but gets his gloves on it. Maybe Trent was undone by the extra bounce on that one. The ball flies towards the keeper and Rishabh Pant gobbles it up. NEW ZEALAND BOWLED OUT FOR 348!

That has swung like a banana! This is angled into the leg pole line but then moves away. Shaw is squared up as he tries to defend. The ball misses his bat and hits the thigh pad. Big swing for Southee first up.
Once again! Gets it to move away from the middle stump line. Shaw looks to defend but it goes off the outer half towards point.
Lands this on middle, Shaw gets right behind the line and keeps it out. Three good deliveries to begin with by Southee.
Angles this one now into the batter, PS works it to mid on.
India are underway! On the pads, Shaw works it through mid-wicket and takes a single.
FOUR! Agarwal is underway in style! A gift for him. A half volley. Agarwal strokes it through covers and it races away to the fence. A good start for the Indians.
On the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Good length and around off, Agarwal plays it late and towards gully.
Length and around middle, MA keeps it out.
Angles this one away from the right-hander after landing it on off. It is left alone.
Slightly fuller and gets it to tail back in from middle, Agarwal works it towards mid-wicket.
On middle and it is a back of a length. Kept out. A steady over to begin by Boult.
Down the leg side, Shaw looks to flick but misses.
BEAUTY! This starts on off and then moves away. Shaw has to play at it but gets beaten.
Looks to bowl the magic delivery as he tries to swing it away from the leg pole to the off pole. No swing though and it is down the leg side.
Fuller and around off, Shaw goes at it with hard hands. It goes off the inner half through square leg for one.
A little too straight, it is clipped around the corner for one at fine leg.
Uppish but in the gap! On the pads, Shaw flicks it in the air but in the gap in the mid-wicket region for two.
On the pads, it is worked behind square on the leg side for one.
This one is angled away from the off stump. Shaw pushes at it but gets beaten.
Length ball on middle, Shaw blocks it off the back foot towards mid-wicket.
On a length and around off, defended to the leg side this time by Shaw.
Length and on the pads, Shaw clips it towards fine leg and takes a run.
On a good length and around off, Agarwal blocks it off the back foot.
Full and around off, Shaw plays it to covers.
Length and around off, Shaw defends it to mid off.
Fuller length ball on off, Shaw blocks it off the back foot towards the bowler.
Length and around off and middle, Shaw defends it to mid on off the back foot.
Good length and around off, Shaw pushes it to mid off.
Full and on middle and leg, Shaw drives it to mid on. A bit uppish but short of the fielder.
Short of a length ball on off, Agarwal blocks it off the back foot towards point.
FOUR! Overpitched and driven nicely by Agarwal. Boult in search of swing dishes out a very full delivery. Agarwal shows the full face of the bat and drives it through mid off for a boundary.
Length and around off, Agarwal lets it be.
Short ball outside off, Agarwal sways away from it.
Fuller length ball outside off, Agarwal takes a nice stride out and drives it through covers for a couple.
On a good length and angling away from the batter, Agarwal shoulders arms to it.
Short ball but down the leg side, Shaw does not bother to play at it.
FOUR! Southee offers width outside the off pole and Shaw capitalizes on it. Length and wide outside off, Shaw sees the length early and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Shaw defends it off the back foot.
Length ball outside off, Shaw punches the ball to the off side off the back foot.
Full and on middle, driven to mid on.
Length ball around off, it jags back in a bit. Shaw looks to defend it with an angled bat but the ball takes the inside edge and thuds into the pads. The ball later rolls towards the slip cordon.
One-legged pull! Shorter and on the body. Agarwal pulls it with his front leg up in the air towards fine leg for one.
Boult comes around the wicket and lands it on a length and around off, it is pushed towards extra cover.
FOUR! Well played! Shorter and around off, Shaw just uses the pace of the bowler and guides it past point. The ball races away to the fence.

OUT! Taken! The ploy to come around the wicket has worked! The plan against Shaw comes good. That is an excellent catch by Latham as well. Boult bangs it short and on middle, Shaw initially looks to glance but then there is extra bounce. He looks to bail out but in the end ends up playing a nothing shot. It hits the higher part of the bat and goes towards square leg. Latham there takes a good catch diving to his left. Another low score for Shaw. India lose one early, they still trail by another 156 runs.
Lands it on a length and around off, Pujara keeps it out.
Shorter in length and outside off, not played at. End of a successful over by Boult.
OHHH! That is fuller and around off, it swings away late. Mayank is drawn into a drive but gets beaten.
On the pads, this is worked towards mid-wicket where the fielder dives to his right and saves it.
On the pads, Agarwal flicks it through mid-wicket. The fielder there dives over the ball and the batters then take three.
Leading edge but safe! This is on the pads, Pujara looks to flick but does so early. He gets a leading edge which goes wide of cover and lands short of mid off.
Uppish again but short! On the pads, Pujara flicks it uppishly but well short of mid-wicket.
Another edge! On middle, Pujara looks to defend but it goes off the outer half through point for one.
Outside off, it is left alone.
One more ball outside off, not played at.
Third leave in a row as it is once again bowled outside off.
Uppish but away! Pujara living dangerously. A short one on middle, there is extra bounce again. Pujara looks to fend at it but it hits the gloves and goes down to fine leg for one.
One more short one, Agarwal ducks under it.
Good length and on middle, kept out.
Good length and on off, defended.
A short one and on middle, CP lets it go over him.
On a good length and around off, Pujara keeps it out.
A little too straight, it is worked behind square on the leg side for one.

That was very close! Full and on middle, Agarwal plants his front foot way too across. He though does well to get bat on ball, it goes uppishly but away from short mid-wicket and the batters take three. He had to get bat to that or he was a goner.
Goes wide of the crease and bowls this outside off. It is left alone.
Fuller and around off, Agarwal pushes it towards mid off and wants a run but is sent back.
A good short one on middle, Agarwal ducks under it. This one though does not bounce a lot.
Shorter and on middle, MA keeps it out nicely.
Goes back to over the wicket and bangs it short on the body. Agarwal lets it go over him.
Angles this away from the right-hander after landing it on a length. Agarwal looks to defend but it goes off the outer half towards gully.
One more short one and it is ducked under again.
Outside off, not played at.
Way too short and way too wide. Left alone again.
Closer to the off pole this time but not close enough to make the batter play.
Gets it right this time. Lands it on off and then moves it away. Pujara looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On the fuller side on off, Pujara works it to mid on.
A dot to end! Colin starts with a maiden! On a length and around off, defended.
Slightly shorter and outside off, left alone. Some away swing for Jamieson.
Shortish and on off, MA hops and tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the body.
One more shot ball but outside off, Agarwal sways away.
One more delivery on a length and around off, Agarwal pushes it towards covers.
Slips this one down the leg side. Agarwal looks to flick but misses.
Another short one on middle, Agarwal ducks under it.
On middle, Pujara works it to mid-wicket.
Length and on off, Pujara watchfully keeps it out.
Another one on a length and around off, CP keeps it out nicely.
On the fuller side around off, it is driven back towards the bowler.
Along the ground though! That is what the Kiwis are looking for. Fuller and around off, Pujara drives it towards short cover.
A good nut to end! Continues landing it around the off pole and this time gets it to move away. Pujara looks to defend but is beaten.
Length and on off, this is pushed to mid off.
Angled into the pads, Agarwal works it towards mid on.
A couple! Fuller and around off, Agarwal strokes it uppishly but wide of KJ and through mid off for two.
Angled into the off pole. Agarwal drops it towards covers and takes one.
A good short one, Pujara ducks under it and lets it go over him quite comfortably.

NOT OUT! Nothing conclusive and the original decision stays! It was very close but in the end, one feels it is the right call. A short one on middle, Pujara is taken by surprise. He takes his eyes off the ball and tries to fend it but the ball kisses some part of the arm and goes to the keeper. An appeal for a caught behind but it is turned down. New Zealand review. Replays roll in but from the first one it is very difficult to decide whether it is the arm guard or the glove. Hot Spot then shows a mark on the arm guard. Some more replays are seen but the umpire does not find anything conclusive to overturn the on-field decision so New Zealand end up losing their review.
FOUR! Superbly played. Short and wide outside off, Agarwal drives it through the vacant point region for a boundary.
Length ball on off, Agarwal blocks it off the back foot.
Length ball down the leg side, Agarwal misses his flick and the keeper collects it.
Good length and outside off, Agarwal taps it to point.
Another ball that is  around off, Agarwal plays it to point.

Huge appeal but nothing from the umpire. De Grandhomme dishes one down the leg side and Agarwal once again goes for the flick. He though misses it. The ball goes to the keeper where Watling collects it and goes in an appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Off the thigh pad though.
Shorter in length and outside off, Pujara does not play at it.
One more short ball and on middle, Pujara stays back and keeps it out.
Another nasty delivery! Shorter and around off, Pujara looks to fend at it but does well to drop his hands in the end.
Way too short this time and it has been wided.

Confusion but no harm done! On a length and around off, Pujara drops it towards the off side and takes off. Agarwal sends him back just in time. Williamson did rush in and had a shy at the striker's end but misses. Pujara would have been in though.
Good length and on off, blocked.
Shorter in length and on middle, it is not played at.
On off, solidly defended.
Back of a length and on off, kept out.
On the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.
On middle, it is worked through square leg for two.
One more ball on a length and around off, it is kept out.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
A nasty one! Length ball on off, Agarwal does well to defend it off the back foot.
Length ball outside off, Agarwal lets it be.
Length and on middle, Agarwal defends it to mid on.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and angled into the pads, Agarwal flicks it to mid-wicket.
Short ball but the line is down the leg side, Agarwal ducks under it.
Full and wide outside off, it swings away. Left alone.
The batsman has nudged the ball fine down the leg side. They have run through for a single.
Three runs! Shorter and around off, Agarwal pulls it through mid-wicket for three. It is not right off middle and hence, does not get to the fence. Ajaz does the mopping up job.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Angled into the batter, Pujara defends it.
Outside off, not played at.
KJ comes around the wicket now and bangs it short! Agarwal takes on the challenge of pulling it. He drags it through mid-wicket and takes three.
Outside off, left alone.
On a length and around off, blocked.
A good short one on middle, Pujara ducks under it.
On the body, this is worked towards backward square leg.
On the pads again, Pujara works it to backward square leg again.
Fuller and on off, Agarwal strokes it to covers.
Gets this one to come back in a little after landing on middle, it is kept out.
OHHH! Just outside off and tailing away further. Agarwal looks to block but is beaten.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Another ball on middle, kept out.
Outside off, left alone.
A bumper and it is ducked under.
Shorter in length again, Pujara works it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length and on middle, kept out.
Shorter and on middle, Pujara stays back and keeps it out.
One more bumper, it is ducked under.
Shortish and outside off, Pujara does not play at it.
FOUR! Width on offer and Agarwal cuts it uppishly through gully and into the fence at third man for a boundary.
Length and on off, Agarwal defends it off the front foot.
Length ball on off, Agarwal blocks it to covers.
Outside off, Agarwal lets it go through.
Good length ball outside off, Agarwal makes a leave.
Length and outside off, played to point.
Good length ball off, Pujara keeps it out off the front foot.
Short of a length ball on middle and leg, Che keeps it out on the leg side.
Full and on the pads, Pujara flicks it to mid-wicket.
Bumper! Pujara lets it sail over him.
Full and on the pads, Pujara flicks it to mid-wicket.
Short of a length ball on leg, Pujara keeps it out off the back foot towards the leg side.
Full ball down the leg side, Agarwal defends it to short leg.
Tossed up ball on off, Agarwal plays it to point.
FOUR! Flatter and shorter on middle, Agarwal rocks onto the back foot and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Floated ball on off, Agarwal taps it to point.
SIX! Floated ball on middle and off, Agarwal dances down the track and lofts it over the bowler for maximum at long off.
On middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
A short one on the body, Pujara ducks under it.
Shortish and on the body, Pujara works it towards square leg.
On the pads again, Pujara works it to square leg.
Close! That came back in sharply. Behind a length and outside off. It comes back in late. Pujara looks to keep it out but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
One more short ball, Pujara ducks under it with ease.
Turn and bounce! It lands on middle, and then turns away. There is also extra bounce. Agarwal looks to defend but gets hit on the body.

FOUR! Fifty for Agarwal, his 4th in Tests! Another good knock from him. Showed promise in the first innings and doing well in the second as well. Gets there by sweeping this ball on the leg stump fine towards the fine leg fence. He needs to keep going now.
Shorter and around off, this is pushed to covers.
Quicker and on off, defended.
Slower through the air and on middle, kept out.
Flatter and on middle, Agarwal stays back and defends it.
Shorter in length and on middle, Pujara keeps it out.
One more short one on middle, Pujara ducks under it.
Nicely played! Boult goes full and outside off, Pujara strokes it through covers and takes two.
On the fuller side, Pujara strokes it to mid off.
Back of a length and on middle, Pujara stays back and keeps it out.
One more delivery outside off, not played at.
Floats it up on middle, this is eased down to long on for one.
Pujara comes down the track but does not get to the pitch of it. He keeps it out.
Nicely bowled! Slows it up and lands it on middle, Pujara looks to defend but it goes off the outer half towards first slip where the fielder makes a good stop diving to his right.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Pujara comes down the track and works this through square leg for three.
On off, Agarwal pushes it to covers.
Full and on  off, Pujara defends it to mid on off the front foot.
Full and outside off, Pujara blocks it off the front foot towards covers.
Outside off, Pujara plays it back to the bowler.
Short ball on middle and leg, Pujara ducks under it.
Length ball on off, Pujara keeps it out off the front foot.

OUT! KABOOM! A wicket just at the stroke of Tea! We saw a wicket on the first ball of the first session and now a wicket of the last ball of the second session. This is poor from Pujara. An error there by him. Can't leave a ball bowled by a left-arm seamer who is tailing the ball back in and bowling from around the wicket. Also, it was not that far away from the off pole to begin with. Pujara does not cover his off pole and shoulders arms to it. The ball finds the stumps. Boult is pumped up and this is exactly what the Kiwis needed. End of a stand which was looking solid. Pujara's poor run in New Zealand continues. He walks back and along with the rest of the players as IT IS TEA ON DAY 3 AND INDIA TRAIL BY 105!
On the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.
On a length and angling into Kohli. He pushes it to mid on.
FOUR! In the air but in the gap! Full and outside off, it swings away further. Kohli strokes it, it goes uppishly past short cover and cover and into the fence.
A little too straight this time, Kohli works it through square leg for two. The trail is now under 100!
Outside off, left alone.
One more ball outside off, it is left alone.
Loose stroke! Short and wide outside off, Agarwal goes after it away from his body but gets beaten.
Good length and on off, Agarwal guides it to point.

Edged but short! Good stop in the end! Back of a length around off, Agarwal plays a touch away from his body. It goes off the outside edge but falls short of Nicholls at gully who dives to his left and stops it.
A short one now and MA ducks under it.
One more delivery on a length outside off. Left alone.
One more back of a length ball around off, Agarwal guides it towards point. Kohli wants a run but is sent back by his partner.
Good length and on off, Kohli defends it.
Outside off again, it is left alone.

EDGY FOUR! Kohli is living dangerously here. This is full and it is moving away from around off. Kohli looks to flick but closes the face of the bat early. He gets a leading edge which goes between widish first slip and gully and down to the third man fence.
On the pads, this time he works it nicely through square leg for one.
Shorter in length and on the body, it is pulled down to fine leg for one.
One more ball on middle, Kohli works it through mid-wicket for a single.
Shorter and outside off, Kohli lets it be.
A short ball, Kohli ducks under it.
Fuller and on off, it is driven to mid off.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Uppish again but on the bounce! Fuller and on off, Kohli drives but fails to keep it down. It does not carry to mid off.
On the stumps, it is kept out.
A short one on the body, Agarwal evades it.
Length ball on off, Agarwal blocks it off the back foot.
Short ball on the hips, Agarwal looks to flick it to the leg side. The ball lobs behind off the thigh pad where the keeper collects it by putting in a dive.
Short and on middle, Agarwal lets it be.
FOUR! That's pulled with disdain. Short ball on middle and leg, Agarwal rides the bounce and pulls it over square leg for a boundary.
Length ball down the leg side, Agarwal does not fiddle with it.
Outside off and on a length. Not played at.
One more ball outside off, left alone.
A little too short and a little too wide. Left alone.
Angled into the off pole. Kohli lunges and keeps it out.
One more delivery outside off, it is not played at.
Outside off again, Kohli does not fiddle with it.
Length and on off, defended off the back foot towards the leg side.
Southee goes short and on middle and leg, Agarwal goes for the pull but fails to get any wood behind the ball.
Short and on leg, Agarwal lets it be.

OUT! India lose their one of the two reviews as there is a spike when the ball passes the bat and Agarwal is a goner! I'll write it once again, not sure why he reviewed, he has a puzzled look on his face as he walks back but that sound could have been nothing but of the edge as the bat was not even close to touching the ground. A soft dismissal in the end. It is a full ball down the leg side, Agarwal looks to flick. There is a tickle on it. Watling takes it and appeals. Up goes the finger. Agarwal stands there for a minute, not sure why? He then starts walking. Kohli stops him and has a word. Mayank then signals the 'T'. Time for the replays and they show that the on-field call is the right one. A good innings by Agarwal comes to an end but India needed him to stay longer. They are in trouble now as they trail by another 87!
A short ball to welcome Rahane. He defends it out.
Another bumper on middle, it is ducked under.
Length and outside off, left alone by Kohli.
FOUR! Virat plays his trademark cover drive. Full and around off, Kohli takes a stride forward and then drives it crisply through covers for a boundary. 100 up for India!
Length and on off, Kohli keeps it out off the front foot.
Full and on the pads, Kohli flicks it on the leg side and gets to the other end.
Length and outside off, Rahane cuts it straight to point.
Some chin music but the line is down the leg side, Rahane ducks under it.
Good length and on off, it is kept out.
One more short one on middle, Kohli hops and keeps it out.
Shorter in length and on the body, Kohli works it towards the leg gully fielder.
A short one and on middle, Kohli ducks under it.
Way down the leg side, Kohli lets it be. Not wided.
Another short ball on the body. Kohli hops and keeps it out.
A short one on the body, Rahane does not play a shot and it hits him on the body.
Down the leg side, it has been left alone.
Short in length outside off, Rahane evades it awkwardly.
One more short ball, Rahane this time looks to pull but misses.
FOUR! Up and over! Ajinkya Rahane won't back down. He will play his shots. This is a clever shot though. It is short and angling away from off. Rahane cuts it over point and bags a boundary.
One more short ball, Rahane keeps it out.
Length ball outside off, Kohli shoulders arms to it.
Length and on middle and leg, Kohli flicks it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and on the pads, Kohli flicks it to square leg and takes a run. The keeper runs to that side and has a shy at the striker's end but misses it.
Good length ball on off, Rahane blocks it off the back foot.
On a length and on off, Rahane is happy to play that off the front foot and into the ground.
On middle, it is worked towards the man at mid-wicket.
Back of a length and on off, Kohli taps it towards covers and takes one.
Short and outside off, Rahane leaves it alone. Way too short though. Wided.
On off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
One more bumper on middle, it is ducked under.
Back of a length and on off, kept out.
Down the leg side, Kohli lets it go.
Length and outside off, Rahane takes a big stride forward. The ball swings away and brushes the pads on its way to the keeper.
Full and on off, Rahane flicks it to the leg side.
Another ball that is on the pads, Rahane flicks it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Length ball outside off, width on offer too. Rahane frees his arms and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Length ball on off, Rahane blocks it off the back foot.
Another ball that is on a length and on off, Rahane keeps it out off the front foot.
Fuller and on off, Kohli strokes it to covers.

OUT! TAKEN! New Zealand are over the moon! Kane Williamson take a bow, Trent Boult take a bow! He was brought back into the attack for this very reason. They needed either of the Indian skipper or the vice captain and Boult has got the big fish, the Indian skipper. Boult comes steaming in from around the wicket and bangs it short. Kohli looks to pull but the ball kisses the gloves and goes into the gloves of the keeper. An appeal and up goes the finger. Once again Kohli fails to make an impact on this tour. India trail by 70. New Zealand will be hoping for a few more wickets before Stumps!

Isn't Vihari watching from the dressing room? Didn't he see Pujara's wicket. It is not a good option leaving Boult's deliveries especially when he is bowling from around the wicket. This time he gets away with it as the ball goes agonizingly close past the off pole.
On off, Vihari keeps it out.
One more bumper, it is ducked under.
On middle, Vihari works it towards mid-wicket.

NOT OUT! It indeed is going down leg. Poor review from the Kiwis! They are now left with no reviews. It is full and around leg stump. Vihari misses the flick and gets hit on the pads. An appeal but it is turned down. The Kiwis review. Replays roll in and they show the on-field call is the right one.
Outside off, it is left alone.
One more delivery around off, it is defended nicely.
On the fuller side, Vihari drives it towards the fielder at covers. He makes a good stop diving to his right.
One more ball outside off, it is not played at.
The batsman works it down the leg side. One run added to the total.
Length ball going down the leg side, Vihari flicks it and the ball goes on the bounce to the keeper who collects it by diving to his left.
Length ball outside off, Vihari lets it be.
Short ball on middle, Vihari ducks under it.
Length ball around off, Vihari blocks it off the back foot.
Full and on the pads, Vihari flicks it to the leg side.
Short ball once again and Vihari sits under it.
Length ball on off, Rahane keeps it out off the back foot.
Length and on off, Rahane blocks it off the back foot.

Huge appeal for a caught behind down the leg side but the umpire is unmoved. De Grandhomme bowls one down the leg side and Rahane misses the flick. The keeper collects it and appeals. The umpire says not out. New Zealand have no reviews left.

Another appeal and this time it is for LBW. De Grandhomme bowls one on a length and on off, Rahane looks to defend it but he fails to lay bat on ball. The ball strikes him high on the pads. The bowler appeals desperately but the umpire once again shakes the head.
Short and outside off, Rahane guides it through point and gets a couple.
Length ball on off, Rahane defends it off the front foot.

Almost a collision! Fuller and around off, Vihari strokes it towards mid off. The batters set off. Rahane and Vihari almost run into each other but they change directions in the end. Also, luckily for them, Williamson had to dive to stop the ball or he would have had a chance.
Fuller and around off, it tails back in. Rahane plays it towards mid on.
This is outstanding stuff! The last one came back in, this one is angled away from the off pole. Rahane hangs his bat out and gets beaten.
Shorter in length and around middle, Rahane pulls. The fielder at mid-wicket makes a half stop. A single taken.
Shorter and around off, defended.
FOUR! Tickled fine! On the pads, Vihari works it nice and fine on the leg side for a boundary.
Length ball outside off, Rahane is happy to let that go.
Length ball on off, Rahane defends it right under his eyes.
Length ball on middle, Rahane looks to defend but the ball takes the inside edge and rolls towards fine leg. The batters take a single.
On a good length and on off, Vihari defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Vihari leaves it for the keeper.
Full and on the pads, Vihari flicks it to the leg side and gets to the other end.
A sharp bumper on middle, Vihari evades it.
Good length and on off, blocked.
Shorter and on middle, this is tucked towards square leg.
Back of a length and on off, Vihari stays back and keeps it out nicely.
On the fuller side on off, Vihari strokes it to mid off.
Good running! Shorter in length and on off, Vihari drops it on the off side and takes one.
Outside off, it is left alone.
On a good length around off, Vihari keeps it out.
One more ball on a good length. It is kept out.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Outside off, not played at.
Length ball outside off, HV lets it go through to the keeper.
Outside off, not played at.
Lovely delivery! Gets it to angle into the batter and then it pitches and moves away. Rahane looks to defend but misses.
Shorter and on off, Rahane pushes it towards cover.
On a length again and around off, kept out.
Full and on middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Rahane drives towards extra cover.
Short and outside off, it is evaded.
On off, kept out.
The batsman works it down the leg side.
Outside off, left alone.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Back of a length and on off, Vihari guides it towards point. He wants a run but then decides against it.
Length ball on off, Rahane keeps it out off the front foot.

OHH! Rahane gets hit on the helmet. Back of a length ball on middle, Rahane goes for the pull but completely loses the sight of the ball. The ball hits his helmet in the end. Colin de Grandhomme comes from short leg to inquire about his well being. Southee too inquires and Rahane shakes his head. The physio comes in and Rahane is ready to resume his innings.
Length ball outside off, Rahane lets it be.
Rahane blocks this length ball on off from with in the crease.
Length ball down the leg side and Rahane leaves it alone.
Outside off, Rahane does not fiddle with it.
Good length and just outside off, it is left alone.
Outside off again but it is left alone again.
Back of a length and on off, Vihari keeps it out.
Played down the wrong line! Fuller and around off, Vihari looks to drive but does so inside the line. Gets beaten.
Outside off, not played at again.
A short one to end! Vihari sways away from it.
Length and outside off, Rahane lets it be.
Length ball on off, Rahane blocks it off the back foot.
Good length ball on off, Rahane defends it off the front foot once again.
Short ball on middle, Rahane pulls it through mid-wicket and gets a single. First run after 33 balls.
Length ball outside off, Vihari shoulders arms to it.
Wide outside off, Vihari watches the ball as he leaves it for the keeper.
FOUR! A much-needed boundary! Short and outside off, Rahane cuts it well over the point fielder and bags a boundary. India trail by another 52.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! Nice controlled shot again. It is short and outside off, Rahane gets on top of the bounce and plays it through point for a boundary.
Good length and on off, it is kept out.
On the pads, it is worked towards mid-wicket.
On off, this is defended nicely.
Outside off, left alone.
BEATEN! Absolute ripper from Southee! He bowls it fuller  and around off, Vihari is committed to defend that off the front foot. The ball at the last moment seams away past the outside edge.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball on off, Vihari keeps it out off the back foot.
Another ball on off, this time Vihari defends it off the front foot.

A direct hit would have been close. Southee bowls one on a length and around off, Vihari strokes it to mid off and hares for a run. Williamson there has a shy at the bowler's end but he misses it. A run is taken in the end.
Length ball outside off, Rahane lets it be.
Short one outside off, the batter evades it.
Fuller and on off, it is driven back to the bowler.
Shortish in length. Vihari evades it.
Angled into the off pole, Vihari keeps it out.
On off, Vihari plays it late through point for one.
Shortish and outside off, Rahane looks to play the upper cut but misses.
Fuller length ball outside off, Vihari keeps it out.
Length ball on off, defended off the front foot towards the off side.
Short of a length ball on middle, Vihari hops and keeps it out on the leg side.
Full ball on the pads, Vihari strokes it to mid on.
Another full ball on the pads, Vihari flicks it towards mid on.
Good length ball on off, Vihari blocks it off the back foot.
Length ball outside off, Rahane leaves it for the keeper.
Back of a length ball on off, Rahane hops and defends it off to point.
Short ball on off, Rahane ducks under it.
Short of a length ball on off, Rahane taps it to covers.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Length ball on leg, Rahane keeps it out on the leg side and scampers for a run.
Length and outside off, Rahane blocks it.
Length ball on off, Rahane defends it off the back foot.
Full and outside off, Rahane strokes it through cover-point and takes a single.
Length ball on middle, Rahane flicks it to the leg side.
Length ball on off, Rahane keeps it out off the back foot.
On a good length ball on off, Rahane blocks it off the front foot.
Length ball down the leg side and Vihari lets it go.
Another one which is bowled down the leg side and Vihari does not fiddle with it.

OHH! Excitement among the Kiwi players. Jamieson bowls one short of a length delivery and it rears up on Vihari who looks to defend but gets it off the gloves towards leg gully. It doesn't carry to the fielder. Would not have mattered though as the bottom hand was off the handle when the ball made contact.
Short ball on middle, HV lets it be.
Length ball down the leg side, Vihari leaves it alone.
FOUR! A boundary on the last ball of the day. Jamieson goes short and wide outside off, Vihari cuts it square on the off side and gets a boundary. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 3!
Boult starts with a back of a length ball outside off, Rahane drops his wrists and leaves it.
Fuller and on the pads, Rahane flicks it to mid-wicket.
Length ball on off, swinging into the batter, Rahane flicks it straight to mid-wicket.
Length ball on off, Rahane plays it with the full face of the bat towards mid off.
FOUR! First runs of the day. Fuller in length and outside off, Rahane leans and drives it past gully and fetches a boundary.
Short ball on middle and leg, Rahane goes for the pull but connects with thin air in the end.
Length ball around off, Vihari plays it off the back foot towards the off side.
Length ball outside off, Vihari lets it be.
On a good length and down the leg side, Vihari misses his flick as the keeper collects it.
Another ball which is bowled outside off and Vihari lets it be.
Full and around off and middle, Vihari plays it to mid on.
Full and around off, Vihari drives it to find short cover to perfection. A maiden to start off with for Southee.
Length and on off and middle, Rahane goes across his stumps and pushes it to mid on.

OUT! CAUGHT! Boult gets his 4th and what a start for New Zealand. Boult has been brilliant in this innings with the ball. This time he bowls one a bit fuller and just about manages it to straighten it off the surface. Rahane who is committed on the front foot to defend it gets beaten by the away swing and edges it to BJ Watling behind the wicket. India still trail by 35 and have lost half their side.
Length ball on off, Pant defends it off the front foot to the off side.
Length ball on off, Pant defends it  off the front foot.

Huge shout for an LBW but the umpire is not interested. Boult bowls one on a length and gets it to swing into the batter. Pant looks to flick it but gets rapped on the pads. The bowler and his teammates appeal but the umpire thinks it otherwise.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground. End of a successful over from Boult.
Length ball outside off, Vihari lets it be.
Full and outside off, Vihari looks to drive it but gets beaten on the outside edge.

OUT! CASTLED! Both the overnight batsmen depart in quick succession and India in deep waters now. Vihari was playing watchfully here. He loses his concentration and sees his off stump take the beating. Southee bowls one on a length and gets it to jag back into the batter. Vihari is stranded on the back foot as he looks to push it to the off side. The ball takes the inside edge and hits the top of off stump.
Length and on off, Ashwin pushes it off the front foot to the off side.

FOUR! Poor delivery and Ashwin gets off the mark here. Southee bowls one down the leg side and Ashwin just gets some bat on the ball. The ball flies past the diving keeper and into the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Ashwin  this time.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Good length and around off, blocked.
A bumper outside off, it is left alone.
Down the leg side, Pant looks to flick but misses.
Slightly fuller and on middle, Pant strokes it to mid on.
A single to end! Short and on the body, this is pulled down to fine leg for one.
Outside off, it is played towards covers.
Starts from outside off, it tails back in a long way. The length is very full. Pant jams it out towards the bowler.
On middle, it is driven to mid on.
FOUR! Hammered! Short and outside off, Pant pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Outside off, Pant guides it to the fielder at gully.

FOUR! Edged and it goes well over! Slash hard if you are going to and that is exactly what Pant does here. It is short and well outside off, Pant goes after it. It goes off the outside edge and over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Back of a length and on off, this is guided towards gully.
On the body of Ashwin, it is worked towards leg gully.
On middle, Ashwin works it to mid on.
On the fuller side, Ashwin strokes it to mid off.
Good length and on off, Ashwin keeps it out nicely.
On the fuller side, it tails back in from outside off. Ashwin plays it nicely towards mid off where Williamson runs to his right, dives and stops it.
Inside edge! Fuller and around off, Pant plays it away from his body. It goes off the inside edge, between his legs and towards the leg side for one.
Angled into the batter, Ashwin works it to mid-wicket.

OUT! LBW! Another one bites the dust! Southee gets Ashwin for the second time. India in serious danger of losing the game by an innings! Southee got Ashwin with an outswinger in the first innings and this time the inswinger does the trick. It is full and it starts tailing back in from off. Ashwin plants his front foot a little too across and then tries to flick. Misses. The ball hits him on the pads. An appeal goes up and so does the finger. New Zealand only need another three wickets. They still lead by 31. Ashwin could consider himself a touch unlucky as Hawk Eye shows that is just clipping the leg pole.

A huge shout but this time not given! Clearly going down leg. It is full again and tailing back in. It is on the pads though. Ishant looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. He also slips in the process.
On the pads, it is worked towards mid-wicket.
Outside off, Sharma guides it to second slip.
Length ball on middle, Pant fends it away to square leg.
Back of length ball outside off, Pant drives it to covers and denies the single here.
Full and angled into the pads, Pant flicks it to deep mid-wicket and does not take the single once again.
Full and on off, Pant pushes it back to the bowler.
Fuller in length and swinging away outside off, Pant hangs his bat out to defend but the ball sneaks past the outside edge.
Full and angled into the pads, Pant flicks it towards fine leg and retains the strike.
Fuller in length and outside off, Pant defends it to covers.
Full and on off, Pant plays the free flowing drive but finds mid off.
Full and on the pads, Pant flicks it to the leg side and takes a run. The fielder in the deep has as wild thow at the striker's end and that allows him to get back for the second with ease.
Short ball on middle and leg, Pant ducks under it.
FOUR! Length ball and around off, Pant gets on one knee and swings it hard through mid-wicket and fetches a boundary.
Length delivery outside off, not in the zone of the batter and Pant makes an easy leave.
Full and angled into the pads, Sharma flicks it to find short leg.
Full and outside off, Sharma drives it through covers and gets a couple this time.
Length ball around off, angling into the batter. Ishant defends it to the leg side off the back foot.
FOUR! Ishant Sharma is no mug with the bat. Boult bowls one outside off and on a fuller length, Sharma drives it through covers and gets a boundary.
Length ball outside off, Ishant covers his off pole and defends it off the back foot towards covers.
Length ball on middle, Sharma flicks it straight to short leg.
Short ball outside off, Pant upper cuts it over the slip cordon and towards the third man region and gets a couple.
Short ball on middle, Pant flicks it to deep square leg and gets a single.
BEATEN! Jamieson bowls one outside off, Sharma makes some room and looks to go over covers but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length ball down the leg side, Ishant looks to pull but gets beaten once again.
Length ball outside off, Sharma gets beaten for the third time in a row.
Length ball down the leg side and Sharma lets it be.
Down the leg side, Pant looks to flick but misses.
On the pads, this time Pant takes the single as he works it towards fine leg.
DROPPED! Another life for Ishant! The change in bowling almost works! Full and around off, Ishant strokes it uppishly to the right of short cover but Southee spills it. Should have taken that.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Fuller and around off, Ishant looks to drive but it goes off the inner half through square leg for one.
A bumper to end! It is on middle, Pant evades it.
Shorter and around off, Ishant guides it to gully.
FOUR! Smashed! Shorter and around off, Ishant makes room and hits it well over mid off for a boundary. INDIA ARE INTO THE LEAD!
Ishant makes room again and Jamieson follows him. Sharma works it through square leg for one.
Shorter and outside off, this is guided through point but the run is not taken.
FOUR! Shorter in length and on the body, Pant pulls it fine on the leg side and bags a boundary.
Good length and on off, Pant drops it towards cover. He wants a run but is sent back.
Outside off, it is left alone.

OUT! That is plumb in front! Colin de Grandhomme's first wicket in this game. Ishant walks a little too far across the stumps. Colin attacks the middle pole. Ishant misses to put bat on ball. It hits him flush in front of the wickets. An appeal and up goes the finger. Ishant stands there and has a word with Pant but the latter asks him not to review and Ishant turns and walks back. India are effectively 6 for 8.
Short and on the body, Shami works it down to fine leg for one.
Shorter and outside off, it is slapped towards cover.
Good fielding! Shorter in length and on middle, Pant pulls it hard towards mid-wicket but the fielder dives to his right and stops it.
Outside off, left alone.
BEATEN! Fuller and around off, it shapes away. Shami looks to drive but is beaten.
On the pads, this is worked fine on the leg side for one.

OUT! TAKEN! A good catch by Boult! Pant holes out. The second new ball does the trick for the hosts. It is on the pads, Pant flicks it uppishly towards fine leg. Boult there, takes a good catch diving forward. The last recognized batter is out of here.
On middle, Bumrah works it to mid-wicket.
That misses the stump by a whisker! Fuller and around off, it shapes away. Bumrah looks to drive but is beaten.

OUT! CAUGHT! That is a ruppa from Mitchell, the substitute! A one-hander. Also, FIFER FOR SOUTHEE. He has taken 9 for the game. An excellent performance from the veteran. He has really led from the front. He bowls a full ball here outside off, Bumrah looks to guide it down to third man but it goes uppishly to the right of Daryl who sticks his right hand out and low. It sticks. INDIA HAVE BEEN BOWLED OUT FOR 191! NEW ZEALAND 9 RUNS TO WIN!
On middle, it is pushed down to long on.
FOUR! Another five runs needed! Full and outside off, it is a half volley. Latham creams it through covers and the ball races away to the fence.
Just behind a driving length this time and on off, Latham strokes it to covers.

Three now! On the pads, this is worked through square leg. Longer side of the ground and hence, the ball slows down as it gets to the fence. Three taken. Two to win now. Two balls left in this over. Can they win it in this over itself?
Outside off, it is left alone.

SCORES LEVEL! There will be a second over in this innings! On the pads, Blundell looks to flick but misses to get hit on the thigh pad. It rolls on the off side. No signal from the umpire so there will be an inside edge.
Back of a length and on off, Blundell guides it to point.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
Shorter and around off, Blundell strokes it to covers.
There it is! Blundell scores the winning runs! On the pads, this is worked towards deep backward square leg for one. NEW ZEALAND WIN BY 10 WICKETS!
